73 /************************************************************************
74  * PRIVATE DEFINITIONS *

76 #define ALLOC_COPY_BIGINT(PTR, VALUE) \
77  do { \
78  PTR = MALLOC(sizeof(INT64)); \
79  if (PTR != NULL) { \
80  *((INT64*) (PTR)) = VALUE; \
81  } \
82  } while (0)
83 
84 #define ALLOC_COPY_UBIGINT(PTR, VALUE) \
85  do { \
86  PTR = MALLOC(sizeof(UINT64)); \
87  if (PTR != NULL) { \
88  *((UINT64*) (PTR)) = VALUE; \
89  } \
90  } while (0)
91 
92 #define ALLOC_COPY_INT(PTR, VALUE) \
93  do { \
94  PTR = MALLOC(sizeof(int)); \
95  if (PTR != NULL) { \
96  *((int*) (PTR)) = VALUE; \
97  } \
98  } while (0)
99 
100 #define ALLOC_COPY_UINT(PTR, VALUE) \
101  do { \
102  PTR = MALLOC(sizeof(unsigned int)); \
103  if (PTR != NULL) { \
104  *((unsigned int*) (PTR)) = VALUE; \
105  } \
106  } while (0)
107 
108 #define ALLOC_COPY_FLOAT(PTR, VALUE) \
109  do { \
110  PTR = MALLOC(sizeof(float)); \
111  if (PTR != NULL) { \
112  *((float*) (PTR)) = VALUE; \
113  } \
114  } while (0)
115 
116 #define ALLOC_COPY_DOUBLE(PTR, VALUE) \
117  do { \
118  PTR = MALLOC(sizeof(double)); \
119  if (PTR != NULL) { \
120  *((double*) (PTR)) = VALUE; \
121  } \
122  } while (0)
123 
124 #define ALLOC_COPY_DATE(PTR, VALUE) \
125  do { \
126  PTR = MALLOC(sizeof(T_CCI_DATE)); \
127  if (PTR != NULL) { \
128  *((T_CCI_DATE*) (PTR)) = VALUE; \
129  } \
130  } while (0)
131 
132 #define ALLOC_COPY_DATE_TZ(PTR, VALUE) \
133  do { \
134  PTR = MALLOC(sizeof(T_CCI_DATE_TZ)); \
135  if (PTR != NULL) { \
136  *((T_CCI_DATE_TZ*) (PTR)) = VALUE; \
137  } \
138  } while (0)
139 
140 #define ALLOC_COPY_OBJECT(PTR, VALUE) \
141  do { \
142  PTR = MALLOC(sizeof(T_OBJECT)); \
143  if (PTR != NULL) { \
144  *((T_OBJECT*) (PTR)) = VALUE; \
145  } \
146  } while (0)
147 
148 #define ALLOC_COPY_BIT(DEST, SRC, SIZE) \
149  do { \
150  DEST = MALLOC(SIZE); \
151  if (DEST != NULL) { \
152  memcpy(DEST, SRC, SIZE); \
153  } \
154  } while (0)

240 int
241 qe_con_close (T_CON_HANDLE * con_handle)
242 {
243  T_NET_BUF net_buf;
244  char func_code = CAS_FC_CON_CLOSE;
245 
246  if (IS_INVALID_SOCKET (con_handle->sock_fd))
247  return 0;
248 
249  net_buf_init (&net_buf);
250  net_buf_cp_str (&net_buf, &func_code, 1);
251 
252  if (net_buf.err_code < 0)
253  goto con_close_end;
254 
255  if (net_send_msg (con_handle, net_buf.data, net_buf.data_size) < 0)
256  goto con_close_end;
257 
258  net_recv_msg (con_handle, NULL, NULL, NULL);
259 
260 con_close_end:
261 
262  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
263  CLOSE_SOCKET (con_handle->sock_fd);
264  con_handle->sock_fd = INVALID_SOCKET;
265 
266  return 0;
267 }
268 
269 int
270 qe_end_tran (T_CON_HANDLE * con_handle, char type, T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)
271 {
272  T_NET_BUF net_buf;
273  char func_code = CAS_FC_END_TRAN;
274  int err_code;
275  bool keep_connection;
276  time_t cur_time, failure_time;
277 #ifdef END_TRAN2
278  char type_str[2];
279 #endif
280 
281  if (IS_INVALID_SOCKET (con_handle->sock_fd))
282  {
283  con_handle->con_status = CCI_CON_STATUS_OUT_TRAN;
284  return CCI_ER_COMMUNICATION;
285  }
286 
287  net_buf_init (&net_buf);
288 
289  net_buf_cp_str (&net_buf, &func_code, 1);
290 
291 #ifdef END_TRAN2
292  type_str[0] = type_str[1] = type;
293  ADD_ARG_BYTES (&net_buf, type_str, 2);
294 #else
295  ADD_ARG_BYTES (&net_buf, &type, 1);
296 #endif
297 
298  if (net_buf.err_code < 0)
299  {
300  err_code = net_buf.err_code;
301  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
302  hm_force_close_connection (con_handle);
303  return err_code;
304  }
305 
306  err_code = net_send_msg (con_handle, net_buf.data, net_buf.data_size);
307  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
308  if (err_code < 0)
309  {
310  hm_force_close_connection (con_handle);
311  return err_code;
312  }
313 
314  err_code = net_recv_msg (con_handle, NULL, NULL, err_buf);
315 
316  if (con_handle->broker_info[BROKER_INFO_STATEMENT_POOLING] != CAS_STATEMENT_POOLING_ON)
317  {
318  if (type == CCI_TRAN_ROLLBACK)
319  {
320  hm_req_handle_free_all (con_handle);
321  }
322  else
323  {
324  hm_req_handle_free_all_unholdable (con_handle);
325  }
326  }
327  else
328  {
329  if (type == CCI_TRAN_ROLLBACK)
330  {
331  /* close all results sets */
332  hm_req_handle_close_all_resultsets (con_handle);
333  }
334  else
335  {
336  /* close only unholdable results sets */
337  hm_req_handle_close_all_unholdable_resultsets (con_handle);
338  }
339  }
340 
341  keep_connection = true;
342 
343  if (con_handle->alter_host_id > 0 && con_handle->rc_time > 0)
344  {
345  cur_time = time (NULL);
346  failure_time = con_handle->last_failure_time;
347 
348  if (failure_time > 0 && (cur_time - failure_time) > con_handle->rc_time)
349  {
350  if (hm_is_host_reachable (con_handle, 0))
351  {
352  keep_connection = false;
353  con_handle->alter_host_id = -1;
354  con_handle->force_failback = 0;
355  con_handle->last_failure_time = 0;
356  }
357  }
358  }
359 
360  if (keep_connection == false)
361  {
362  hm_force_close_connection (con_handle);
363  }
364 
365  con_handle->con_status = CCI_CON_STATUS_OUT_TRAN;
366  return err_code;
367 }
368 
369 int
370 qe_end_session (T_CON_HANDLE * con_handle, T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)
371 {
372  T_NET_BUF net_buf;
373  char func_code = CAS_FC_END_SESSION;
374  int err_code;
375  if (hm_is_empty_session (&con_handle->session_id))
376  {
377  return 0;
378  }
379  net_buf_init (&net_buf);
380 
381  net_buf_cp_str (&net_buf, &func_code, 1);
382 
383  if (net_buf.err_code < 0)
384  {
385  err_code = net_buf.err_code;
386  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
387  return err_code;
388  }
389 
390  err_code = net_send_msg (con_handle, net_buf.data, net_buf.data_size);
391  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
392  if (err_code < 0)
393  {
394  return err_code;
395  }
396 
397  err_code = net_recv_msg (con_handle, NULL, NULL, err_buf);
398 
399  hm_make_empty_session (&con_handle->session_id);
400  return err_code;
401 }
402 
403 int
404 qe_prepare (T_REQ_HANDLE * req_handle, T_CON_HANDLE * con_handle, char *sql_stmt, char flag, T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf,
405  int reuse)
406 {
407  T_NET_BUF net_buf;
408  char func_code = CAS_FC_PREPARE;
409  char autocommit_flag;
410  int sql_stmt_size;
411  int err_code;
412  char *result_msg = NULL;
413  int result_msg_size;
414  int result_code;
415  int remaining_time = 0;
416 
417  if (!reuse)
418  {
419  FREE_MEM (req_handle->sql_text);
420  ALLOC_COPY (req_handle->sql_text, sql_stmt);
421  }
422 
423  if (req_handle->sql_text == NULL)
424  {
425  return CCI_ER_NO_MORE_MEMORY;
426  }
427 
428  sql_stmt_size = strlen (req_handle->sql_text) + 1;
429 
430  net_buf_init (&net_buf);
431 
432  net_buf_cp_str (&net_buf, &func_code, 1);
433 
434  ADD_ARG_STR (&net_buf, req_handle->sql_text, sql_stmt_size, con_handle->charset);
435 
436  if (hm_get_con_handle_holdable (con_handle))
437  {
438  /* make sure statement is holdable */
439  flag |= CCI_PREPARE_HOLDABLE;
440  }
441  ADD_ARG_BYTES (&net_buf, &flag, 1);
442 
443  autocommit_flag = (char) con_handle->autocommit_mode;
444  ADD_ARG_BYTES (&net_buf, &autocommit_flag, 1);
445 
446  while (con_handle->deferred_close_handle_count > 0)
447  {
448  ADD_ARG_INT (&net_buf, con_handle->deferred_close_handle_list[--con_handle->deferred_close_handle_count]);
449  }
450 
451  if (net_buf.err_code < 0)
452  {
453  err_code = net_buf.err_code;
454  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
455  return err_code;
456  }
457 
458  if (TIMEOUT_IS_SET (con_handle))
459  {
460  remaining_time = con_handle->current_timeout;
461  remaining_time -= get_elapsed_time (&con_handle->start_time);
462  if (remaining_time <= 0)
463  {
464  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
465  return CCI_ER_QUERY_TIMEOUT;
466  }
467  }
468 
469  err_code = net_send_msg (con_handle, net_buf.data, net_buf.data_size);
470  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
471  if (err_code < 0)
472  {
473  return err_code;
474  }
475 
476  result_code = net_recv_msg_timeout (con_handle, &result_msg, &result_msg_size, err_buf, remaining_time);
477  if (result_code < 0)
478  {
479  return result_code;
480  }
481 
482  result_msg_size -= 4;
483  err_code = prepare_info_decode (result_msg + 4, &result_msg_size, req_handle);
484  if (err_code < 0)
485  {
486  FREE_MEM (result_msg);
487  return err_code;
488  }
489 
490  FREE_MEM (result_msg);
491 
492  req_handle->handle_type = HANDLE_PREPARE;
493  req_handle->handle_sub_type = 0;
494  req_handle->server_handle_id = result_code;
495  req_handle->cur_fetch_tuple_index = -1;
496  if ((flag & CCI_PREPARE_UPDATABLE) != 0)
497  {
498  flag |= CCI_PREPARE_INCLUDE_OID;
499  }
500  req_handle->prepare_flag = flag;
501  req_handle->cursor_pos = 0;
502  req_handle->is_closed = 0;
503  req_handle->valid = 1;
504  req_handle->is_from_current_transaction = 1;
505 
506  if (!reuse)
507  {
508  if (req_handle->num_bind > 0)
509  {
510  req_handle->bind_value = (T_BIND_VALUE *) MALLOC (sizeof (T_BIND_VALUE) * req_handle->num_bind);
511 
512  if (req_handle->bind_value == NULL)
513  {
514  return CCI_ER_NO_MORE_MEMORY;
515  }
516 
517  memset (req_handle->bind_value, 0, sizeof (T_BIND_VALUE) * req_handle->num_bind);
518 
519  req_handle->bind_mode = (char *) MALLOC (req_handle->num_bind);
520  if (req_handle->bind_mode == NULL)
521  {
522  return CCI_ER_NO_MORE_MEMORY;
523  }
524 
525  memset (req_handle->bind_mode, CCI_PARAM_MODE_UNKNOWN, req_handle->num_bind);
526  }
527  }
528 
529  return CCI_ER_NO_ERROR;
530 }
531 
532 int
533 qe_bind_param (T_REQ_HANDLE * req_handle, int index, T_CCI_A_TYPE a_type, void *value, int length, T_CCI_U_TYPE u_type,
534  char flag)
535 {
536  int err_code;
537 
538  assert (u_type >= CCI_U_TYPE_FIRST && u_type <= CCI_U_TYPE_LAST);
539 
540  index--;
541 
542  if (index < 0 || index >= req_handle->num_bind)
543  {
544  return CCI_ER_BIND_INDEX;
545  }
546 
547  if (req_handle->bind_value[index].flag == BIND_PTR_DYNAMIC)
548  {
549  FREE_MEM (req_handle->bind_value[index].value);
550  memset (&(req_handle->bind_value[index]), 0, sizeof (T_BIND_VALUE));
551  }
552 
553  req_handle->bind_mode[index] = CCI_PARAM_MODE_IN;
554 
555  if (value == NULL || u_type == CCI_U_TYPE_NULL)
556  {
557  req_handle->bind_value[index].u_type = CCI_U_TYPE_NULL;
558  return 0;
559  }
560 
561  err_code = bind_value_conversion (a_type, u_type, flag, value, length, &(req_handle->bind_value[index]));
562 
563  return err_code;
564 }
565 
566 int
567 qe_execute (T_REQ_HANDLE * req_handle, T_CON_HANDLE * con_handle, char flag, int max_col_size, T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)
568 {
569  T_NET_BUF net_buf;
570  char func_code = CAS_FC_EXECUTE;
571  char autocommit_flag;
572  int i;
573  int err_code = 0;
574  int res_count;
575  char *result_msg = NULL, *msg;
576  int result_msg_size;
577  T_CCI_QUERY_RESULT *qr = NULL;
578  char fetch_flag;
579  char forward_only_cursor;
580  char include_column_info;
581  int remain_msg_size = 0;
582  int remaining_time = 0;
583  bool use_server_query_cancel = false;
584  int shard_id;
585  T_BROKER_VERSION broker_ver;
586 
587  req_handle->is_fetch_completed = 0;
588  QUERY_RESULT_FREE (req_handle);
589 
590  net_buf_init (&net_buf);
591 
592  net_buf_cp_str (&net_buf, &func_code, 1);
593 
594  ADD_ARG_INT (&net_buf, req_handle->server_handle_id);
595  ADD_ARG_BYTES (&net_buf, &flag, 1);
596  ADD_ARG_INT (&net_buf, max_col_size);
597  ADD_ARG_INT (&net_buf, req_handle->max_row);
598  if (req_handle->first_stmt_type == CUBRID_STMT_CALL_SP)
599  {
600  ADD_ARG_BYTES (&net_buf, req_handle->bind_mode, req_handle->num_bind);
601  }
602  else
603  {
604  ADD_ARG_BYTES (&net_buf, NULL, 0);
605  }
606 
607  if (req_handle->first_stmt_type == CUBRID_STMT_SELECT)
608  {
609  fetch_flag = 1;
610  }
611  else
612  {
613  fetch_flag = 0;
614  }
615  ADD_ARG_BYTES (&net_buf, &fetch_flag, 1);
616 
617  if (con_handle->autocommit_mode == CCI_AUTOCOMMIT_TRUE)
618  {
619  forward_only_cursor = true;
620  }
621  else
622  {
623  forward_only_cursor = false;
624  }
625  autocommit_flag = (char) con_handle->autocommit_mode;
626  ADD_ARG_BYTES (&net_buf, &autocommit_flag, 1);
627  ADD_ARG_BYTES (&net_buf, &forward_only_cursor, 1);
628 
629  ADD_ARG_CACHE_TIME (&net_buf, 0, 0);
630 
631  if (TIMEOUT_IS_SET (con_handle))
632  {
633  remaining_time = con_handle->current_timeout;
634  remaining_time -= get_elapsed_time (&con_handle->start_time);
635  if (remaining_time <= 0)
636  {
637  err_code = CCI_ER_QUERY_TIMEOUT;
638  goto execute_error;
639  }
640  }
641 
642  broker_ver = hm_get_broker_version (con_handle);
643  if (hm_broker_understand_the_protocol (broker_ver, PROTOCOL_V2))
644  {
645  /* In PROTOCOL_V2, cci driver use server query timeout feature, when disconnect_on_query_timeout is false. */
646  if (TIMEOUT_IS_SET (con_handle) && con_handle->disconnect_on_query_timeout == false)
647  {
648  use_server_query_cancel = true;
649  }
650  ADD_ARG_INT (&net_buf, remaining_time);
651  }
652  else if (hm_broker_understand_the_protocol (broker_ver, PROTOCOL_V1))
653  {
654  /* cci does not use server query timeout in PROTOCOL_V1 */
655  ADD_ARG_INT (&net_buf, 0);
656  }
657 
658  for (i = 0; i < req_handle->num_bind; i++)
659  {
660  bind_value_to_net_buf (&net_buf, req_handle->bind_value[i].u_type, req_handle->bind_value[i].value,
661  req_handle->bind_value[i].size, con_handle->charset,
662  is_set_default_value_if_null (con_handle, req_handle->stmt_type,
663  req_handle->bind_mode[i]));
664  }
665 
666  if (net_buf.err_code < 0)
667  {
668  err_code = net_buf.err_code;
669  goto execute_error;
670  }
671 
672  err_code = net_send_msg (con_handle, net_buf.data, net_buf.data_size);
673  if (err_code < 0)
674  {
675  goto execute_error;
676  }
677 
678  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
679 
680  res_count =
681  net_recv_msg_timeout (con_handle, &result_msg, &result_msg_size, err_buf,
682  ((use_server_query_cancel) ? 0 : remaining_time));
683 
684  if (res_count < 0)
685  {
686  return res_count;
687  }
688 
689  err_code = execute_array_info_decode (result_msg + 4, result_msg_size - 4, EXECUTE_EXEC, &qr, &remain_msg_size);
690  if (err_code < 0 || remain_msg_size < 0)
691  {
692  FREE_MEM (result_msg);
693  if (err_code == CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
694  {
695  return CCI_ER_COMMUNICATION;
696  }
697 
698  return err_code;
699  }
700 
701  if (qr == NULL)
702  {
703  req_handle->num_query_res = 0;
704  req_handle->qr = NULL;
705  }
706  else
707  {
708  req_handle->num_query_res = err_code;
709  req_handle->qr = qr;
710  }
711 
712  if (req_handle->first_stmt_type == CUBRID_STMT_SELECT || req_handle->first_stmt_type == CUBRID_STMT_GET_STATS
713  || req_handle->first_stmt_type == CUBRID_STMT_CALL || req_handle->first_stmt_type == CUBRID_STMT_EVALUATE)
714  {
715  req_handle->num_tuple = res_count;
716  }
717  else if (req_handle->first_stmt_type == CUBRID_STMT_CALL_SP)
718  {
719  req_handle->num_tuple = res_count;
720  }
721  else
722  {
723  req_handle->num_tuple = -1;
724  }
725 
726  req_handle->execute_flag = flag;
727 
728  hm_req_handle_fetch_buf_free (req_handle);
729  req_handle->cursor_pos = 0;
730 
731  if (hm_broker_understand_the_protocol (broker_ver, PROTOCOL_V2))
732  {
733  msg = result_msg + (result_msg_size - remain_msg_size);
734 
735  NET_STR_TO_BYTE (include_column_info, msg);
736  remain_msg_size -= NET_SIZE_BYTE;
737  msg += NET_SIZE_BYTE;
738 
739  if (include_column_info == 1)
740  {
741  err_code = prepare_info_decode (msg, &remain_msg_size, req_handle);
742  if (err_code < 0)
743  {
744  FREE_MEM (result_msg);
745  return err_code;
746  }
747  }
748  }
749 
750  if (hm_broker_understand_the_protocol (broker_ver, PROTOCOL_V5))
751  {
752  msg = result_msg + (result_msg_size - remain_msg_size);
753 
754  NET_STR_TO_INT (shard_id, msg);
755  remain_msg_size -= NET_SIZE_INT;
756  msg += NET_SIZE_INT;
757 
758  con_handle->shard_id = shard_id;
759  req_handle->shard_id = shard_id;
760  }
761 
762  /* If fetch_flag is 1, executing query and fetching data is processed together. So, fetching results are included in
763  * result_msg. */
764  if (req_handle->first_stmt_type == CUBRID_STMT_SELECT)
765  {
766  int num_tuple;
767 
768  req_handle->cursor_pos = 1;
769  num_tuple =
770  decode_fetch_result (con_handle, req_handle, result_msg, result_msg + (result_msg_size - remain_msg_size) + 4,
771  remain_msg_size - 4);
772  req_handle->cursor_pos = 0;
773  if (num_tuple < 0)
774  {
775  FREE_MEM (result_msg);
776  return num_tuple;
777  }
778  }
779  else
780  {
781  FREE_MEM (result_msg);
782  }
783 
784  req_handle->is_closed = 0;
785  req_handle->is_from_current_transaction = 1;
786 
787  return res_count;
788 
789 execute_error:
790  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
791  return err_code;
792 }
793 
794 int
795 qe_prepare_and_execute (T_REQ_HANDLE * req_handle, T_CON_HANDLE * con_handle, char *sql_stmt, int max_col_size,
796  T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)
797 {
798  T_NET_BUF net_buf;
799  char func_code = CAS_FC_PREPARE_AND_EXECUTE;
800  char autocommit_flag;
801  int sql_stmt_size;
802  int err_code;
803  int result_code;
804  int execute_res_count;
805  char *result_msg = NULL;
806  char *msg;
807  char *result_msg_org;
808  int result_msg_size;
809  T_CCI_QUERY_RESULT *qr = NULL;
810  char fetch_flag;
811  char include_column_info;
812  int remain_msg_size = 0;
813  int remaining_time = 0;
814  int num_tuple = 0;
815  char prepare_flag = 0;
816  char execute_flag = CCI_EXEC_QUERY_ALL;
817  int prepare_argc_count = 3;
818  bool use_server_query_cancel = false;
819  int shard_id;
820  T_BROKER_VERSION broker_ver;
821 
822  QUERY_RESULT_FREE (req_handle);
823 
824  ALLOC_COPY (req_handle->sql_text, sql_stmt);
825 
826  if (req_handle->sql_text == NULL)
827  {
828  return CCI_ER_NO_MORE_MEMORY;
829  }
830 
831  sql_stmt_size = strlen (req_handle->sql_text) + 1;
832 
833  net_buf_init (&net_buf);
834 
835  /* prepare info */
836  broker_ver = hm_get_broker_version (con_handle);
837  if (hm_broker_match_the_protocol (broker_ver, PROTOCOL_V2))
838  {
839  func_code = CAS_FC_PREPARE_AND_EXECUTE_FOR_PROTO_V2;
840  }
841  net_buf_cp_str (&net_buf, &func_code, 1);
842  prepare_argc_count += con_handle->deferred_close_handle_count;
843  ADD_ARG_INT (&net_buf, prepare_argc_count);
844  ADD_ARG_STR (&net_buf, req_handle->sql_text, sql_stmt_size, con_handle->charset);
845  ADD_ARG_BYTES (&net_buf, &prepare_flag, 1);
846  autocommit_flag = (char) con_handle->autocommit_mode;
847  ADD_ARG_BYTES (&net_buf, &autocommit_flag, 1);
848 
849  while (con_handle->deferred_close_handle_count > 0)
850  {
851  ADD_ARG_INT (&net_buf, con_handle->deferred_close_handle_list[--con_handle->deferred_close_handle_count]);
852  }
853 
854  /* execute info */
855  ADD_ARG_BYTES (&net_buf, &execute_flag, 1);
856  ADD_ARG_INT (&net_buf, max_col_size);
857  ADD_ARG_INT (&net_buf, req_handle->max_row);
858  ADD_ARG_BYTES (&net_buf, NULL, 0);
859 
860  ADD_ARG_CACHE_TIME (&net_buf, 0, 0);
861 
862  if (TIMEOUT_IS_SET (con_handle))
863  {
864  remaining_time = con_handle->current_timeout;
865  remaining_time -= get_elapsed_time (&con_handle->start_time);
866  if (remaining_time <= 0)
867  {
868  err_code = CCI_ER_QUERY_TIMEOUT;
869  goto prepare_and_execute_error;
870  }
871  }
872 
873  if (hm_broker_understand_the_protocol (broker_ver, PROTOCOL_V2))
874  {
875  /* In PROTOCOL_V2, cci driver use server query timeout feature, when disconnect_on_query_timeout is false. */
876  if (TIMEOUT_IS_SET (con_handle) && con_handle->disconnect_on_query_timeout == false)
877  {
878  use_server_query_cancel = true;
879  }
880  ADD_ARG_INT (&net_buf, remaining_time);
881  }
882  else if (hm_broker_understand_the_protocol (broker_ver, PROTOCOL_V1))
883  {
884  /* cci does not use server query timeout in PROTOCOL_V1 */
885  ADD_ARG_INT (&net_buf, 0);
886  }
887 
888  if (net_buf.err_code < 0)
889  {
890  err_code = net_buf.err_code;
891  goto prepare_and_execute_error;
892  }
893 
894  err_code = net_send_msg (con_handle, net_buf.data, net_buf.data_size);
895  if (err_code < 0)
896  {
897  goto prepare_and_execute_error;
898  }
899 
900  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
901 
902 
903  /* prepare result */
904  result_code =
905  net_recv_msg_timeout (con_handle, &result_msg, &result_msg_size, err_buf,
906  ((use_server_query_cancel) ? 0 : remaining_time));
907 
908  if (result_code < 0)
909  {
910  return result_code;
911  }
912 
913  result_msg_org = result_msg;
914  result_msg += 4;
915  result_msg_size -= 4;
916  remain_msg_size = result_msg_size;
917 
918  err_code = prepare_info_decode (result_msg, &result_msg_size, req_handle);
919 
920  if (err_code < 0)
921  {
922  FREE_MEM (result_msg_org);
923  return err_code;
924  }
925 
926  req_handle->handle_type = HANDLE_PREPARE;
927  req_handle->handle_sub_type = 0;
928  req_handle->server_handle_id = result_code;
929  req_handle->cur_fetch_tuple_index = -1;
930  if ((prepare_flag & CCI_PREPARE_UPDATABLE) != 0)
931  {
932  prepare_flag |= CCI_PREPARE_INCLUDE_OID;
933  }
934  req_handle->prepare_flag = prepare_flag;
935  req_handle->cursor_pos = 0;
936  req_handle->is_closed = 0;
937  req_handle->valid = 1;
938  req_handle->is_from_current_transaction = 1;
939 
940  if (req_handle->stmt_type == CUBRID_STMT_SELECT)
941  {
942  fetch_flag = 1;
943  }
944  else
945  {
946  fetch_flag = 0;
947  }
948 
949  /* execute result */
950  result_msg += (remain_msg_size - result_msg_size);
951 
952  memcpy ((char *) &execute_res_count, result_msg + CAS_PROTOCOL_ERR_INDICATOR_INDEX, CAS_PROTOCOL_ERR_INDICATOR_SIZE);
953  execute_res_count = ntohl (execute_res_count);
954 
955  result_msg += 4;
956  result_msg_size -= 4;
957 
958  err_code = execute_array_info_decode (result_msg, result_msg_size, EXECUTE_EXEC, &qr, &remain_msg_size);
959  if (err_code < 0 || remain_msg_size < 0)
960  {
961  FREE_MEM (result_msg_org);
962  if (err_code == CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
963  {
964  return CCI_ER_COMMUNICATION;
965  }
966 
967  return err_code;
968  }
969 
970  if (qr == NULL)
971  {
972  req_handle->num_query_res = 0;
973  req_handle->qr = NULL;
974  }
975  else
976  {
977  req_handle->num_query_res = err_code;
978  req_handle->qr = qr;
979  }
980 
981  if (req_handle->stmt_type == CUBRID_STMT_SELECT || req_handle->stmt_type == CUBRID_STMT_GET_STATS
982  || req_handle->stmt_type == CUBRID_STMT_CALL || req_handle->stmt_type == CUBRID_STMT_EVALUATE)
983  {
984  req_handle->num_tuple = execute_res_count;
985  }
986  else if (req_handle->stmt_type == CUBRID_STMT_CALL_SP)
987  {
988  req_handle->num_tuple = execute_res_count;
989  }
990  else
991  {
992  req_handle->num_tuple = -1;
993  }
994 
995  req_handle->execute_flag = execute_flag;
996 
997  hm_req_handle_fetch_buf_free (req_handle);
998  req_handle->cursor_pos = 0;
999 
1000  if (hm_broker_understand_the_protocol (broker_ver, PROTOCOL_V2))
1001  {
1002  msg = result_msg + (result_msg_size - remain_msg_size);
1003 
1004  NET_STR_TO_BYTE (include_column_info, msg);
1005  remain_msg_size -= NET_SIZE_BYTE;
1006  msg += NET_SIZE_BYTE;
1007 
1008  if (include_column_info == 1)
1009  {
1010  err_code = prepare_info_decode (msg, &remain_msg_size, req_handle);
1011  if (err_code < 0)
1012  {
1013  FREE_MEM (result_msg_org);
1014  return err_code;
1015  }
1016  }
1017  }
1018 
1019  if (hm_broker_understand_the_protocol (broker_ver, PROTOCOL_V5))
1020  {
1021  msg = result_msg + (result_msg_size - remain_msg_size);
1022 
1023  NET_STR_TO_INT (shard_id, msg);
1024  remain_msg_size -= NET_SIZE_INT;
1025  msg += NET_SIZE_INT;
1026 
1027  con_handle->shard_id = shard_id;
1028  req_handle->shard_id = shard_id;
1029  }
1030 
1031  /* If fetch_flag is 1, executing query and fetching data is processed together. So, fetching results are included in
1032  * result_msg. */
1033  if (fetch_flag)
1034  {
1035  req_handle->cursor_pos = 1;
1036  num_tuple =
1037  decode_fetch_result (con_handle, req_handle, result_msg_org,
1038  result_msg + (result_msg_size - remain_msg_size) + 4, remain_msg_size - 4);
1039  req_handle->cursor_pos = 0;
1040  if (num_tuple < 0)
1041  {
1042  FREE_MEM (result_msg_org);
1043  return num_tuple;
1044  }
1045  }
1046  else
1047  {
1048  FREE_MEM (result_msg_org);
1049  }
1050 
1051  return execute_res_count;
1052 
1053 prepare_and_execute_error:
1054  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
1055  return err_code;
1056 }
1057 
1058 
1059 void
1060 qe_bind_value_free (T_REQ_HANDLE * req_handle)
1061 {
1062  int i;
1063 
1064  if (req_handle->bind_value == NULL)
1065  {
1066  return;
1067  }
1068 
1069  for (i = 0; i < req_handle->num_bind; i++)
1070  {
1071  if (req_handle->bind_value[i].flag == BIND_PTR_DYNAMIC)
1072  {
1073  FREE_MEM (req_handle->bind_value[i].value);
1074  req_handle->bind_value[i].flag = BIND_PTR_STATIC;
1075  }
1076  }
1077 }
1078 
1079 int
1080 qe_get_db_parameter (T_CON_HANDLE * con_handle, T_CCI_DB_PARAM param_name, void *ret_val, T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)
1081 {
1082  T_NET_BUF net_buf;
1083  char func_code = CAS_FC_GET_DB_PARAMETER;
1084  char *result_msg = NULL;
1085  int result_msg_size;
1086  int err_code = CCI_ER_NO_ERROR;
1087  int val;
1088  T_BROKER_VERSION broker_ver;
1089 
1090  if (ret_val == NULL)
1091  {
1092  return CCI_ER_NO_ERROR;
1093  }
1094 
1095  net_buf_init (&net_buf);
1096 
1097  net_buf_cp_str (&net_buf, &func_code, 1);
1098 
1099  ADD_ARG_INT (&net_buf, param_name);
1100 
1101  if (net_buf.err_code < 0)
1102  {
1103  err_code = net_buf.err_code;
1104  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
1105  return err_code;
1106  }
1107 
1108  err_code = net_send_msg (con_handle, net_buf.data, net_buf.data_size);
1109  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
1110  if (err_code < 0)
1111  {
1112  return err_code;
1113  }
1114 
1115  err_code = net_recv_msg (con_handle, &result_msg, &result_msg_size, err_buf);
1116  result_msg_size -= NET_SIZE_INT;
1117 
1118  if (err_code >= 0)
1119  {
1120  if (result_msg_size < NET_SIZE_INT)
1121  {
1122  err_code = CCI_ER_COMMUNICATION;
1123  }
1124  else
1125  {
1126  NET_STR_TO_INT (val, result_msg + NET_SIZE_INT);
1127  if (param_name == CCI_PARAM_LOCK_TIMEOUT)
1128  {
1129  broker_ver = hm_get_broker_version (con_handle);
1130  if (!hm_broker_understand_the_protocol (broker_ver, PROTOCOL_V2))
1131  {
1132  if (val > 0)
1133  {
1134  val = val * 1000; /* second --> millisecond */
1135  }
1136  }
1137  }
1138  memcpy (ret_val, (char *) &val, sizeof (int));
1139  }
1140  }
1141 
1142  FREE_MEM (result_msg);
1143 
1144  return err_code;
1145 }
1146 
1147 int
1148 qe_set_db_parameter (T_CON_HANDLE * con_handle, T_CCI_DB_PARAM param_name, void *value, T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)
1149 {
1150  T_NET_BUF net_buf;
1151  char func_code = CAS_FC_SET_DB_PARAMETER;
1152  int err_code;
1153 
1154  net_buf_init (&net_buf);
1155 
1156  net_buf_cp_str (&net_buf, &func_code, 1);
1157  ADD_ARG_INT (&net_buf, param_name);
1158 
1159  switch (param_name)
1160  {
1161  case CCI_PARAM_ISOLATION_LEVEL:
1162  case CCI_PARAM_LOCK_TIMEOUT:
1163  {
1164  int i_val;
1165  i_val = *((int *) value);
1166  ADD_ARG_INT (&net_buf, i_val);
1167  }
1168  break;
1169 #if 0
1170  /* CCI AUTO COMMIT MODE SUPPORT */
1171  case CCI_PARAM_AUTO_COMMIT:
1172  {
1173  int i_val;
1174  i_val = *((int *) value);
1175  ADD_ARG_INT (&net_buf, i_val);
1176 
1177  if (i_val == 0)
1178  {
1179  con_handle->autocommit_mode = CCI_AUTOCOMMIT_FALSE;
1180  }
1181  else
1182  {
1183  con_handle->autocommit_mode = CCI_AUTOCOMMIT_TRUE;
1184  }
1185  }
1186  break;
1187 #endif
1188  default:
1189  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
1190  return CCI_ER_PARAM_NAME;
1191  }
1192 
1193  if (net_buf.err_code < 0)
1194  {
1195  err_code = net_buf.err_code;
1196  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
1197  return err_code;
1198  }
1199 
1200  err_code = net_send_msg (con_handle, net_buf.data, net_buf.data_size);
1201  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
1202  if (err_code < 0)
1203  return err_code;
1204 
1205  err_code = net_recv_msg (con_handle, NULL, NULL, err_buf);
1206 
1207  return err_code;
1208 }
1209 
1210 int
1211 qe_set_cas_change_mode (T_CON_HANDLE * con_handle, int mode, T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)
1212 {
1213  T_NET_BUF net_buf;
1214  char func_code = CAS_FC_CAS_CHANGE_MODE;
1215  int err_code;
1216  char *result_msg, *cur_p;
1217  int result_msg_size;
1218  int prev_mode = 0;
1219 
1220  assert (mode == CAS_CHANGE_MODE_AUTO || mode == CAS_CHANGE_MODE_KEEP);
1221 
1222  net_buf_init (&net_buf);
1223 
1224  net_buf_cp_str (&net_buf, &func_code, 1);
1225 
1226  ADD_ARG_INT (&net_buf, mode);
1227 
1228  err_code = net_send_msg (con_handle, net_buf.data, net_buf.data_size);
1229  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
1230  if (err_code < 0)
1231  {
1232  return err_code;
1233  }
1234 
1235  result_msg = NULL;
1236  result_msg_size = 0;
1237  err_code = net_recv_msg (con_handle, &result_msg, &result_msg_size, err_buf);
1238  if (err_code < 0)
1239  {
1240  return err_code;
1241  }
1242  if (result_msg == NULL)
1243  {
1244  return CCI_ER_COMMUNICATION;
1245  }
1246 
1247  cur_p = result_msg + NET_SIZE_INT;
1248  result_msg_size -= NET_SIZE_INT;
1249 
1250  if (result_msg_size < NET_SIZE_INT)
1251  {
1252  FREE_MEM (result_msg);
1253  return CCI_ER_COMMUNICATION;
1254  }
1255  NET_STR_TO_INT (prev_mode, cur_p);
1256  FREE_MEM (result_msg);
1257 
1258  return prev_mode;
1259 }
1260 
1261 int
1262 qe_close_query_result (T_REQ_HANDLE * req_handle, T_CON_HANDLE * con_handle)
1263 {
1264  int err_code = 0;
1265  T_NET_BUF net_buf;
1266  char func_code = CAS_FC_CURSOR_CLOSE;
1267  T_BROKER_VERSION broker_ver;
1268 
1269  if (!hm_get_con_handle_holdable (con_handle))
1270  {
1271  return err_code;
1272  }
1273 
1274  if (is_connected_to_cubrid (con_handle) == false)
1275  {
1276  return err_code;
1277  }
1278 
1279  net_buf_init (&net_buf);
1280 
1281  broker_ver = hm_get_broker_version (con_handle);
1282  if (hm_broker_match_the_protocol (broker_ver, PROTOCOL_V2))
1283  {
1284  func_code = CAS_FC_CURSOR_CLOSE_FOR_PROTO_V2;
1285  }
1286 
1287  net_buf_cp_str (&net_buf, &func_code, 1);
1288  ADD_ARG_INT (&net_buf, req_handle->server_handle_id);
1289 
1290  if (net_buf.err_code < 0)
1291  {
1292  err_code = net_buf.err_code;
1293  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
1294  return err_code;
1295  }
1296 
1297  err_code = net_send_msg (con_handle, net_buf.data, net_buf.data_size);
1298  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
1299  if (err_code < 0)
1300  {
1301  return err_code;
1302  }
1303 
1304  err_code = net_recv_msg (con_handle, NULL, NULL, NULL);
1305 
1306  return err_code;
1307 }
1308 
1309 int
1310 qe_close_req_handle (T_REQ_HANDLE * req_handle, T_CON_HANDLE * con_handle)
1311 {
1312  return qe_close_req_handle_internal (req_handle, con_handle, false);
1313 }
1314 
1315 static int
1316 qe_close_req_handle_internal (T_REQ_HANDLE * req_handle, T_CON_HANDLE * con_handle, bool force_close)
1317 {
1318  int err_code = 0;
1319  int *new_deferred_close_handle_list = NULL;
1320  int new_deferred_max_close_handle_count;
1321 
1322  /* same to qe_close_con. when statement pool is on, (cci_end_tran -> cci_close_req_handle) can be appeared. If
1323  * connection was closed in cci_end_tran (keep_connection=off), failure(using closed socket) returns while sending a
1324  * message in this function. So, if sockect is closed at this point, messages must not be sent to server. */
1325  if (IS_INVALID_SOCKET (con_handle->sock_fd) || !req_handle->valid)
1326  {
1327  return 0;
1328  }
1329 
1330  if (req_handle->stmt_type == CUBRID_STMT_SELECT || req_handle->stmt_type == CUBRID_STMT_GET_STATS
1331  || req_handle->stmt_type == CUBRID_STMT_CALL || req_handle->stmt_type == CUBRID_STMT_CALL_SP
1332  || req_handle->stmt_type == CUBRID_STMT_EVALUATE || force_close)
1333  {
1334  goto send_close_handle_msg;
1335  }
1336 
1337  if (con_handle->deferred_close_handle_count == 0
1338  && con_handle->deferred_max_close_handle_count != DEFERRED_CLOSE_HANDLE_ALLOC_SIZE)
1339  {
1340  /* shrink the list size */
1341  new_deferred_close_handle_list =
1342  (int *) REALLOC (con_handle->deferred_close_handle_list, sizeof (int) * DEFERRED_CLOSE_HANDLE_ALLOC_SIZE);
1343  if (new_deferred_close_handle_list == NULL)
1344  {
1345  goto send_close_handle_msg;
1346  }
1347  con_handle->deferred_max_close_handle_count = DEFERRED_CLOSE_HANDLE_ALLOC_SIZE;
1348  con_handle->deferred_close_handle_list = new_deferred_close_handle_list;
1349  }
1350  else if (con_handle->deferred_close_handle_count + 1 > con_handle->deferred_max_close_handle_count)
1351  {
1352  /* grow the list size */
1353  new_deferred_max_close_handle_count =
1354  con_handle->deferred_max_close_handle_count + DEFERRED_CLOSE_HANDLE_ALLOC_SIZE;
1355  new_deferred_close_handle_list =
1356  (int *) REALLOC (con_handle->deferred_close_handle_list, sizeof (int) * new_deferred_max_close_handle_count);
1357  if (new_deferred_close_handle_list == NULL)
1358  {
1359  goto send_close_handle_msg;
1360  }
1361  con_handle->deferred_max_close_handle_count = new_deferred_max_close_handle_count;
1362  con_handle->deferred_close_handle_list = new_deferred_close_handle_list;
1363  }
1364 
1365  con_handle->deferred_close_handle_list[con_handle->deferred_close_handle_count++] = req_handle->server_handle_id;
1366 
1367  return err_code;
1368 
1369 send_close_handle_msg:
1370 
1371  err_code = qe_send_close_handle_msg (con_handle, req_handle->server_handle_id);
1372 
1373  return err_code;
1374 }
1375 
1376 void
1377 qe_close_req_handle_all (T_CON_HANDLE * con_handle)
1378 {
1379  int i;
1380  T_REQ_HANDLE *req_handle;
1381 
1382  /* close handle in req handle table */
1383  for (i = 0; i < con_handle->max_req_handle; i++)
1384  {
1385  if (con_handle->req_handle_table[i] == NULL)
1386  {
1387  continue;
1388  }
1389  req_handle = con_handle->req_handle_table[i];
1390 
1391  map_close_ots (req_handle->mapped_stmt_id);
1392  req_handle->mapped_stmt_id = -1;
1393  qe_close_req_handle_internal (req_handle, con_handle, false);
1394  }
1395  hm_req_handle_free_all (con_handle);
1396 }
1397 
1398 static int
1399 qe_send_close_handle_msg (T_CON_HANDLE * con_handle, int server_handle_id)
1400 {
1401  int err_code = 0;
1402  T_NET_BUF net_buf;
1403  char func_code = CAS_FC_CLOSE_REQ_HANDLE;
1404  char autocommit_flag;
1405 
1406  net_buf_init (&net_buf);
1407 
1408  net_buf_cp_str (&net_buf, &func_code, 1);
1409  ADD_ARG_INT (&net_buf, server_handle_id);
1410  autocommit_flag = (char) con_handle->autocommit_mode;
1411  ADD_ARG_BYTES (&net_buf, &autocommit_flag, 1);
1412 
1413  if (net_buf.err_code < 0)
1414  {
1415  err_code = net_buf.err_code;
1416  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
1417  return err_code;
1418  }
1419 
1420  err_code = net_send_msg (con_handle, net_buf.data, net_buf.data_size);
1421  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
1422  if (err_code < 0)
1423  {
1424  return err_code;
1425  }
1426 
1427  err_code = net_recv_msg (con_handle, NULL, NULL, NULL);
1428 
1429  return err_code;
1430 }
1431 
1432 int
1433 qe_cursor (T_REQ_HANDLE * req_handle, T_CON_HANDLE * con_handle, int offset, char origin, T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)
1434 {
1435  char func_code = CAS_FC_CURSOR;
1436  int err_code;
1437  char *result_msg = NULL;
1438  int result_msg_size;
1439  T_NET_BUF net_buf;
1440  char *cur_p;
1441  int tuple_num;
1442  int cursor_pos;
1443 
1444  if (req_handle->is_closed)
1445  {
1446  return CCI_ER_RESULT_SET_CLOSED;
1447  }
1448 
1449  if (req_handle->handle_type == HANDLE_PREPARE)
1450  {
1451  if (req_handle->stmt_type == CUBRID_STMT_SELECT || req_handle->stmt_type == CUBRID_STMT_GET_STATS
1452  || req_handle->stmt_type == CUBRID_STMT_CALL || req_handle->stmt_type == CUBRID_STMT_CALL_SP
1453  || req_handle->stmt_type == CUBRID_STMT_EVALUATE)
1454  {
1455  if (req_handle->num_tuple >= 0)
1456  {
1457  cursor_pos = get_cursor_pos (req_handle, offset, origin);
1458  if (cursor_pos <= 0)
1459  {
1460  req_handle->cursor_pos = 0;
1461  return CCI_ER_NO_MORE_DATA;
1462  }
1463  else if (cursor_pos > req_handle->num_tuple)
1464  {
1465  req_handle->cursor_pos = req_handle->num_tuple + 1;
1466  return CCI_ER_NO_MORE_DATA;
1467  }
1468 
1469  if (is_connected_to_oracle (con_handle) && cursor_pos > req_handle->fetched_tuple_end
1470  && req_handle->is_fetch_completed)
1471  {
1472  return CCI_ER_NO_MORE_DATA;
1473  }
1474 
1475  req_handle->cursor_pos = cursor_pos;
1476  return 0;
1477  }
1478  else
1479  { /* async query */
1480  if (origin != CCI_CURSOR_LAST)
1481  {
1482  cursor_pos = get_cursor_pos (req_handle, offset, origin);
1483  req_handle->cursor_pos = cursor_pos;
1484  if (req_handle->fetched_tuple_begin > 0 && cursor_pos >= req_handle->fetched_tuple_begin
1485  && cursor_pos <= req_handle->fetched_tuple_end)
1486  {
1487  return 0;
1488  }
1489  if (cursor_pos <= 0)
1490  {
1491  req_handle->cursor_pos = 0;
1492  return CCI_ER_NO_MORE_DATA;
1493  }
1494  }
1495  }
1496  }
1497  else
1498  {
1499  return CCI_ER_NO_MORE_DATA;
1500  }
1501  }
1502  else if (req_handle->handle_type == HANDLE_SCHEMA_INFO || req_handle->handle_type == HANDLE_COL_GET)
1503  {
1504  cursor_pos = get_cursor_pos (req_handle, offset, origin);
1505  if (cursor_pos <= 0 || cursor_pos > req_handle->num_tuple)
1506  {
1507  if (cursor_pos <= 0)
1508  req_handle->cursor_pos = 0;
1509  else if (cursor_pos > req_handle->num_tuple)
1510  req_handle->cursor_pos = req_handle->num_tuple + 1;
1511 
1512  return CCI_ER_NO_MORE_DATA;
1513  }
1514  req_handle->cursor_pos = cursor_pos;
1515  return 0;
1516  }
1517  else if (req_handle->handle_type == HANDLE_OID_GET)
1518  return 0;
1519 
1520  if (origin == CCI_CURSOR_FIRST || origin == CCI_CURSOR_LAST)
1521  {
1522  cursor_pos = offset;
1523  }
1524  else if (origin == CCI_CURSOR_CURRENT)
1525  {
1526  cursor_pos = req_handle->cursor_pos;
1527  origin = CCI_CURSOR_FIRST;
1528  }
1529  else
1530  return CCI_ER_INVALID_CURSOR_POS;
1531 
1532  net_buf_init (&net_buf);
1533  net_buf_cp_str (&net_buf, &func_code, 1);
1534  ADD_ARG_INT (&net_buf, req_handle->server_handle_id);
1535  ADD_ARG_INT (&net_buf, cursor_pos);
1536  ADD_ARG_BYTES (&net_buf, &origin, 1);
1537 
1538  if (net_buf.err_code < 0)
1539  {
1540  err_code = net_buf.err_code;
1541  goto cursor_error;
1542  }
1543 
1544  err_code = net_send_msg (con_handle, net_buf.data, net_buf.data_size);
1545  if (err_code < 0)
1546  {
1547  goto cursor_error;
1548  }
1549  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
1550 
1551  err_code = net_recv_msg (con_handle, &result_msg, &result_msg_size, err_buf);
1552  if (err_code < 0)
1553  {
1554  return err_code;
1555  }
1556  if (result_msg == NULL)
1557  {
1558  return CCI_ER_COMMUNICATION;
1559  }
1560 
1561  cur_p = result_msg + NET_SIZE_INT;
1562  result_msg_size -= NET_SIZE_INT;
1563 
1564  if (result_msg_size < NET_SIZE_INT)
1565  {
1566  FREE_MEM (result_msg);
1567  return CCI_ER_COMMUNICATION;
1568  }
1569  NET_STR_TO_INT (tuple_num, cur_p);
1570  req_handle->num_tuple = tuple_num;
1571  FREE_MEM (result_msg);
1572 
1573  if (origin == CCI_CURSOR_FIRST)
1574  {
1575  if (req_handle->num_tuple >= 0 && req_handle->cursor_pos > req_handle->num_tuple)
1576  {
1577  req_handle->cursor_pos = req_handle->num_tuple + 1;
1578  return CCI_ER_NO_MORE_DATA;
1579  }
1580  req_handle->cursor_pos = cursor_pos;
1581  }
1582  else
1583  {
1584  if (req_handle->num_tuple <= 0 || req_handle->num_tuple - cursor_pos + 1 <= 0)
1585  {
1586  req_handle->cursor_pos = 0;
1587  return CCI_ER_NO_MORE_DATA;
1588  }
1589  req_handle->cursor_pos = req_handle->num_tuple - cursor_pos + 1;
1590  }
1591 
1592  return 0;
1593 
1594 cursor_error:
1595  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
1596  return err_code;
1597 }
1598 
1599 int
1600 qe_fetch (T_REQ_HANDLE * req_handle, T_CON_HANDLE * con_handle, char flag, int result_set_index, T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)
1601 {
1602  T_NET_BUF net_buf;
1603  int err_code;
1604  char func_code = CAS_FC_FETCH;
1605  char *result_msg = NULL;
1606  int result_msg_size;
1607  int num_tuple;
1608 
1609  if (req_handle->cursor_pos <= 0)
1610  {
1611  return CCI_ER_NO_MORE_DATA;
1612  }
1613 
1614  if (req_handle->is_closed)
1615  {
1616  return CCI_ER_RESULT_SET_CLOSED;
1617  }
1618 
1619  if (req_handle->fetched_tuple_begin > 0 && req_handle->cursor_pos >= req_handle->fetched_tuple_begin
1620  && req_handle->cursor_pos <= req_handle->fetched_tuple_end)
1621  {
1622  req_handle->cur_fetch_tuple_index = req_handle->cursor_pos - req_handle->fetched_tuple_begin;
1623  if (flag)
1624  {
1625  if (ut_is_deleted_oid (&(req_handle->tuple_value[req_handle->cur_fetch_tuple_index].tuple_oid)))
1626  {
1627  return CCI_ER_DELETED_TUPLE;
1628  }
1629  }
1630  return 0;
1631  }
1632 
1633  hm_req_handle_fetch_buf_free (req_handle);
1634 
1635  net_buf_init (&net_buf);
1636  net_buf_cp_str (&net_buf, &func_code, 1);
1637  ADD_ARG_INT (&net_buf, req_handle->server_handle_id);
1638  ADD_ARG_INT (&net_buf, req_handle->cursor_pos);
1639  ADD_ARG_INT (&net_buf, req_handle->fetch_size);
1640  ADD_ARG_BYTES (&net_buf, &flag, 1);
1641  ADD_ARG_INT (&net_buf, result_set_index);
1642 
1643  if (net_buf.err_code < 0)
1644  {
1645  err_code = net_buf.err_code;
1646  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
1647  return err_code;
1648  }
1649 
1650  err_code = net_send_msg (con_handle, net_buf.data, net_buf.data_size);
1651  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
1652  if (err_code < 0)
1653  return err_code;
1654 
1655  err_code = net_recv_msg (con_handle, &result_msg, &result_msg_size, err_buf);
1656  if (err_code < 0)
1657  {
1658  return err_code;
1659  }
1660 
1661  num_tuple = decode_fetch_result (con_handle, req_handle, result_msg, result_msg + 4, result_msg_size - 4);
1662  if (num_tuple < 0)
1663  {
1664  FREE_MEM (result_msg);
1665  return num_tuple;
1666  }
1667 
1668  if (num_tuple != 0)
1669  {
1670  if (flag)
1671  {
1672  if (ut_is_deleted_oid (&(req_handle->tuple_value[0].tuple_oid)))
1673  {
1674  return CCI_ER_DELETED_TUPLE;
1675  }
1676  }
1677  }
1678  else
1679  {
1680  if (is_connected_to_oracle (con_handle) && req_handle->cursor_pos > req_handle->fetched_tuple_end
1681  && req_handle->is_fetch_completed)
1682  {
1683  return CCI_ER_NO_MORE_DATA;
1684  }
1685  }
1686 
1687  return 0;
1688 }
1689 
1690 int
1691 qe_get_data (T_CON_HANDLE * con_handle, T_REQ_HANDLE * req_handle, int col_no, int a_type, void *value, int *indicator)
1692 {
1693  char *col_value_p;
1694  T_CCI_U_EXT_TYPE u_ext_type;
1695  T_CCI_U_TYPE u_type;
1696  int data_size;
1697  int err_code;
1698  int num_cols;
1699 
1700  if (req_handle->is_closed)
1701  {
1702  return CCI_ER_RESULT_SET_CLOSED;
1703  }
1704 
1705  if (req_handle->stmt_type == CUBRID_STMT_CALL_SP)
1706  {
1707  num_cols = req_handle->num_bind + 1;
1708  col_no++;
1709  }
1710  else
1711  {
1712  num_cols = req_handle->num_col_info;
1713  }
1714 
1715  if (col_no <= 0 || col_no > num_cols)
1716  {
1717  return CCI_ER_COLUMN_INDEX;
1718  }
1719 
1720  if (req_handle->cur_fetch_tuple_index < 0)
1721  {
1722  return CCI_ER_INVALID_CURSOR_POS;
1723  }
1724 
1725  col_value_p = req_handle->tuple_value[req_handle->cur_fetch_tuple_index].column_ptr[col_no - 1];
1726 
1727  if (req_handle->stmt_type == CUBRID_STMT_CALL_SP)
1728  {
1729  u_ext_type = CCI_U_TYPE_NULL;
1730  }
1731  else
1732  {
1733  u_ext_type = CCI_GET_RESULT_INFO_TYPE (req_handle->col_info, col_no);
1734  }
1735 
1736  NET_STR_TO_INT (data_size, col_value_p);
1737  if (data_size <= 0)
1738  {
1739  *indicator = -1;
1740  if (a_type == CCI_A_TYPE_STR || a_type == CCI_A_TYPE_SET || a_type == CCI_A_TYPE_BLOB
1741  || a_type == CCI_A_TYPE_CLOB)
1742  {
1743  *((void **) value) = NULL;
1744  }
1745  return 0;
1746  }
1747 
1748  col_value_p += NET_SIZE_INT;
1749  if (u_ext_type == CCI_U_TYPE_NULL)
1750  {
1751  char basic_type, set_type;
1752 
1753  if (data_size <= NET_SIZE_BYTE)
1754  {
1755  *indicator = -1;
1756  if (a_type == CCI_A_TYPE_STR || a_type == CCI_A_TYPE_SET || a_type == CCI_A_TYPE_BLOB
1757  || a_type == CCI_A_TYPE_CLOB)
1758  {
1759  *((void **) value) = NULL;
1760  }
1761  return 0;
1762  }
1763 
1764  NET_STR_TO_BYTE (basic_type, col_value_p);
1765  data_size -= NET_SIZE_BYTE;
1766  col_value_p += NET_SIZE_BYTE;
1767 
1768  if (CCI_NET_TYPE_HAS_2BYTES (basic_type))
1769  {
1770  /* type encoded on 2 bytes */
1771  if (data_size <= NET_SIZE_BYTE)
1772  {
1773  *indicator = -1;
1774  if (a_type == CCI_A_TYPE_STR || a_type == CCI_A_TYPE_SET || a_type == CCI_A_TYPE_BLOB
1775  || a_type == CCI_A_TYPE_CLOB)
1776  {
1777  *((void **) value) = NULL;
1778  }
1779  return 0;
1780  }
1781 
1782  NET_STR_TO_BYTE (set_type, col_value_p);
1783  data_size -= NET_SIZE_BYTE;
1784  col_value_p += NET_SIZE_BYTE;
1785 
1786  u_ext_type = get_ext_utype_from_net_bytes ((T_CCI_U_TYPE) basic_type, (T_CCI_U_TYPE) set_type);
1787  }
1788  else
1789  {
1790  /* legacy server */
1791  u_ext_type = basic_type;
1792  }
1793  }
1794 
1795  u_type = get_basic_utype (u_ext_type);
1796 
1797  *indicator = 0;
1798 
1799  confirm_schema_type_info (req_handle, col_no, u_type, col_value_p, data_size);
1800 
1801  switch (a_type)
1802  {
1803  case CCI_A_TYPE_STR:
1804  err_code = qe_get_data_str (&(req_handle->conv_value_buffer), u_type, col_value_p, data_size, value, indicator);
1805  break;
1806  case CCI_A_TYPE_BIGINT:
1807  err_code = qe_get_data_bigint (u_type, col_value_p, value);
1808  break;
1809  case CCI_A_TYPE_UBIGINT:
1810  err_code = qe_get_data_ubigint (u_type, col_value_p, value);
1811  break;
1812  case CCI_A_TYPE_INT:
1813  err_code = qe_get_data_int (u_type, col_value_p, value);
1814  break;
1815  case CCI_A_TYPE_UINT:
1816  err_code = qe_get_data_uint (u_type, col_value_p, value);
1817  break;
1818  case CCI_A_TYPE_FLOAT:
1819  err_code = qe_get_data_float (u_type, col_value_p, value);
1820  break;
1821  case CCI_A_TYPE_DOUBLE:
1822  err_code = qe_get_data_double (u_type, col_value_p, value);
1823  break;
1824  case CCI_A_TYPE_BIT:
1825  err_code = qe_get_data_bit (u_type, col_value_p, data_size, value);
1826  break;
1827  case CCI_A_TYPE_DATE:
1828  err_code = qe_get_data_date (u_type, col_value_p, value);
1829  break;
1830  case CCI_A_TYPE_SET:
1831  err_code = get_data_set (u_type, col_value_p, (T_SET **) value, data_size);
1832  break;
1833  case CCI_A_TYPE_BLOB:
1834  case CCI_A_TYPE_CLOB:
1835  err_code = qe_get_data_lob (u_type, col_value_p, data_size, value);
1836  break;
1837  case CCI_A_TYPE_REQ_HANDLE:
1838  err_code = qe_get_data_req_handle (con_handle, req_handle, col_value_p, value);
1839  break;
1840  case CCI_A_TYPE_DATE_TZ:
1841  err_code = qe_get_data_date_tz (u_type, col_value_p, value, data_size);
1842  break;
1843  default:
1844  return CCI_ER_ATYPE;
1845  }
1846 
1847  return err_code;
1848 }
1849 
1850 int
1851 qe_get_cur_oid (T_REQ_HANDLE * req_handle, char *oid_str_buf)
1852 {
1853  int index;
1854 
1855  if (req_handle->cur_fetch_tuple_index < 0)
1856  {
1857  return CCI_ER_INVALID_CURSOR_POS;
1858  }
1859 
1860  if (req_handle->prepare_flag & CCI_PREPARE_INCLUDE_OID)
1861  {
1862  index = req_handle->cur_fetch_tuple_index;
1863  ut_oid_to_str (&(req_handle->tuple_value[index].tuple_oid), oid_str_buf);
1864  }
1865  else
1866  {
1867  strcpy (oid_str_buf, "");
1868  }
1869 
1870  return 0;
1871 }
1872 
1873 int
1874 qe_schema_info (T_REQ_HANDLE * req_handle, T_CON_HANDLE * con_handle, int type, char *arg1, char *arg2, char flag,
1875  int shard_id, T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)
1876 {
1877  T_NET_BUF net_buf;
1878  char func_code = CAS_FC_SCHEMA_INFO;
1879  int err_code;
1880  int result_code;
1881  char *result_msg;
1882  int result_msg_size;
1883  T_BROKER_VERSION broker_ver;
1884 
1885  net_buf_init (&net_buf);
1886  net_buf_cp_str (&net_buf, &func_code, 1);
1887  ADD_ARG_INT (&net_buf, type);
1888 
1889  if (arg1 == NULL)
1890  ADD_ARG_BYTES (&net_buf, NULL, 0);
1891  else
1892  ADD_ARG_STR (&net_buf, arg1, strlen (arg1) + 1, con_handle->charset);
1893  if (arg2 == NULL)
1894  ADD_ARG_BYTES (&net_buf, NULL, 0);
1895  else
1896  ADD_ARG_STR (&net_buf, arg2, strlen (arg2) + 1, con_handle->charset);
1897  ADD_ARG_BYTES (&net_buf, &flag, 1);
1898 
1899  broker_ver = hm_get_broker_version (con_handle);
1900  if (hm_broker_understand_the_protocol (broker_ver, PROTOCOL_V5))
1901  {
1902  ADD_ARG_INT (&net_buf, shard_id);
1903  }
1904

1906  {
1907  err_code = net_buf.err_code;
1908  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
1909  return err_code;
1910  }
1911 
1912  err_code = net_send_msg (con_handle, net_buf.data, net_buf.data_size);
1913  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
1914  if (err_code < 0)
1915  return err_code;
1916 
1917  result_code = net_recv_msg (con_handle, &result_msg, &result_msg_size, err_buf);
1918  if (result_code < 0)
1919  return result_code;
1920 
1921  err_code = schema_info_decode (result_msg + 4, result_msg_size - 4, req_handle);
1922  FREE_MEM (result_msg);
1923  if (err_code < 0)
1924  return err_code;
1925 
1926  req_handle->handle_type = HANDLE_SCHEMA_INFO;
1927  req_handle->handle_sub_type = type;
1928  req_handle->server_handle_id = result_code;
1929  req_handle->cur_fetch_tuple_index = -1;
1930  req_handle->cursor_pos = 0;
1931  req_handle->valid = 1;
1932 
1933  return 0;

2037 int
2038 qe_oid_put2 (T_CON_HANDLE * con_handle, char *oid_str, char **attr_name, void **new_val, int *a_type,
2039  T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)
2040 {
2041  T_NET_BUF net_buf;
2042  char func_code = CAS_FC_OID_PUT;
2043  int err_code;
2044  int i, data_size = 0;
2045  T_OBJECT oid;
2046  T_CCI_U_TYPE u_type;
2047  void *value;
2048  T_BIND_VALUE tmp_cell;
2049 
2050  if (ut_str_to_oid (oid_str, &oid) < 0)
2051  {
2052  return CCI_ER_OBJECT;
2053  }
2054 
2055  net_buf_init (&net_buf);
2056  net_buf_cp_str (&net_buf, &func_code, 1);
2057 
2058  ADD_ARG_OBJECT (&net_buf, &oid);
2059  for (i = 0; attr_name[i] != NULL; i++)
2060  {
2061  tmp_cell.flag = BIND_PTR_STATIC;
2062  tmp_cell.value = NULL;
2063 
2064  ADD_ARG_STR (&net_buf, attr_name[i], strlen (attr_name[i]) + 1, con_handle->charset);
2065 
2066  value = NULL;
2067 
2068  if (new_val[i] == NULL)
2069  {
2070  u_type = CCI_U_TYPE_NULL;
2071  }
2072  else
2073  {
2074  switch (a_type[i])
2075  {
2076  case CCI_A_TYPE_STR:
2077  data_size = strlen ((char *) (new_val[i])) + 1;
2078  u_type = CCI_U_TYPE_STRING;
2079  value = new_val[i];
2080  break;
2081  case CCI_A_TYPE_BIGINT:
2082  data_size = NET_SIZE_BIGINT;
2083  u_type = CCI_U_TYPE_BIGINT;
2084  value = new_val[i];
2085  break;
2086  case CCI_A_TYPE_INT:
2087  data_size = NET_SIZE_INT;
2088  u_type = CCI_U_TYPE_INT;
2089  value = new_val[i];
2090  break;
2091  case CCI_A_TYPE_FLOAT:
2092  data_size = NET_SIZE_FLOAT;
2093  u_type = CCI_U_TYPE_FLOAT;
2094  value = new_val[i];
2095  break;
2096  case CCI_A_TYPE_DOUBLE:
2097  data_size = NET_SIZE_DOUBLE;
2098  u_type = CCI_U_TYPE_DOUBLE;
2099  value = new_val[i];
2100  break;
2101  case CCI_A_TYPE_BIT:
2102  data_size = ((T_CCI_BIT *) (new_val[i]))->size;
2103  u_type = CCI_U_TYPE_BIT;
2104  value = ((T_CCI_BIT *) (new_val[i]))->buf;
2105  break;
2106  case CCI_A_TYPE_DATE:
2107  data_size = NET_SIZE_DATETIME;
2108  u_type = CCI_U_TYPE_DATETIME;
2109  value = new_val[i];
2110  break;
2111  case CCI_A_TYPE_DATE_TZ:
2112  u_type = CCI_U_TYPE_DATETIMETZ;
2113  value = new_val[i];
2114  data_size = NET_SIZE_DATETIME + NET_SIZE_TZ (value);
2115  break;
2116  case CCI_A_TYPE_SET:
2117  err_code =
2118  bind_value_conversion (CCI_A_TYPE_SET, CCI_U_TYPE_SEQUENCE, CCI_BIND_PTR, new_val[i], UNMEASURED_LENGTH,
2119  &tmp_cell);
2120  if (err_code < 0)
2121  {
2122  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
2123  return err_code;
2124  }
2125  data_size = tmp_cell.size;
2126  value = tmp_cell.value;
2127  u_type = CCI_U_TYPE_SEQUENCE;
2128  break;
2129 
2130  case CCI_A_TYPE_UINT:
2131  case CCI_A_TYPE_UBIGINT:
2132  default:
2133  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
2134  return CCI_ER_ATYPE;
2135  }
2136  }
2137 
2138  bind_value_to_net_buf (&net_buf, u_type, value, data_size, con_handle->charset, false);
2139 
2140  if (tmp_cell.flag == BIND_PTR_DYNAMIC)
2141  {
2142  FREE_MEM (tmp_cell.value);
2143  }
2144  }
2145 
2146  if (net_buf.err_code < 0)
2147  {
2148  err_code = net_buf.err_code;
2149  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
2150  return err_code;
2151  }
2152 
2153  err_code = net_send_msg (con_handle, net_buf.data, net_buf.data_size);
2154  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
2155  if (err_code < 0)
2156  return err_code;
2157 
2158  err_code = net_recv_msg (con_handle, NULL, NULL, err_buf);
2159 
2160  return err_code;
2161 }

2448 int
2449 qe_get_last_insert_id (T_REQ_HANDLE * req_handle, T_CON_HANDLE * con_handle, void *value, T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)
2450 {
2451  T_NET_BUF net_buf;
2452  char func_code = CAS_FC_GET_LAST_INSERT_ID;
2453  int err_code;
2454  char *result_msg = NULL;
2455  int result_msg_size;
2456  int valsize = 0;
2457  unsigned char type = 0;
2458  char *ptr = NULL;
2459  net_buf_init (&net_buf);
2460 
2461  net_buf_cp_str (&net_buf, &func_code, 1);
2462 
2463  /* initialize */
2464  assert (value != NULL);
2465  *(char **) value = NULL;
2466 
2467  if (net_buf.err_code < 0)
2468  {
2469  err_code = net_buf.err_code;
2470  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
2471  return err_code;
2472  }
2473 
2474  err_code = net_send_msg (con_handle, net_buf.data, net_buf.data_size);
2475  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
2476 
2477  if (err_code < 0)
2478  {
2479  return err_code;
2480  }
2481 
2482  err_code = net_recv_msg (con_handle, &result_msg, &result_msg_size, err_buf);
2483 
2484  if (err_code < 0)
2485  {
2486  return err_code;
2487  }
2488 
2489  if (result_msg_size < 4)
2490  {
2491  FREE_MEM (result_msg);
2492  return CCI_ER_COMMUNICATION;
2493  }
2494 
2495  NET_STR_TO_INT (err_code, result_msg);
2496  ptr = result_msg + NET_SIZE_INT;
2497 
2498  /* start decoding numeric value */
2499  NET_STR_TO_INT (valsize, ptr);
2500  if (valsize == -1)
2501  {
2502  /*
2503  * CCI_ER_NO_ERROR with NULL value
2504  * means DB NULL
2505  */
2506  FREE_MEM (result_msg);
2507  return CCI_ER_NO_ERROR;
2508  }
2509 
2510  ptr = ptr + NET_SIZE_INT;
2511  valsize--; /* skip type byte */
2512 
2513  /* decode type */
2514  type = *ptr;
2515 
2516  if (CCI_NET_TYPE_HAS_2BYTES (type))
2517  {
2518  unsigned char set_type;
2519  T_CCI_U_EXT_TYPE u_ext_type;
2520 
2521  /* type encoded on 2 bytes */
2522  if (valsize <= NET_SIZE_BYTE)
2523  {
2524  FREE_MEM (result_msg);
2525  return CCI_ER_NO_ERROR;
2526  }
2527 
2528  ptr++;
2529  valsize--;
2530 
2531  NET_STR_TO_BYTE (set_type, ptr);
2532  u_ext_type = get_ext_utype_from_net_bytes ((T_CCI_U_TYPE) type, (T_CCI_U_TYPE) set_type);
2533  type = CCI_GET_COLLECTION_DOMAIN (u_ext_type);
2534  }
2535  else
2536  {
2537  /* legacy server, type byte already read */
2538  }
2539 
2540  if (type != CCI_U_TYPE_NUMERIC)
2541  {
2542  FREE_MEM (result_msg);
2543  return CCI_ER_COMMUNICATION;
2544  }
2545 
2546  ptr = ptr + NET_SIZE_BYTE;
2547 
2548  /* copy to con_handle->last_insert_id */
2549  if (con_handle->last_insert_id == NULL)
2550  {
2551  /* 2 for sign & null termination */
2552  con_handle->last_insert_id = (char *) MALLOC (MAX_NUMERIC_PRECISION + 2);
2553  if (con_handle->last_insert_id == NULL)
2554  {
2555  err_code = CCI_ER_NO_MORE_MEMORY;
2556  FREE_MEM (result_msg);
2557  return err_code;
2558  }
2559  }
2560 
2561  /* valsize include null terminate byte */
2562  assert (valsize < MAX_NUMERIC_PRECISION + 2);
2563 
2564  strncpy (con_handle->last_insert_id, ptr, valsize - 1);
2565  con_handle->last_insert_id[valsize - 1] = '\0';
2566 
2567  *((char **) value) = con_handle->last_insert_id;
2568 
2569  FREE_MEM (result_msg);
2570  return err_code;
2571 }

2575 qe_col_size (T_CON_HANDLE * con_handle, char *oid_str, const char *col_attr, int *set_size, T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)
2576 {

2579  char col_cmd = CCI_COL_SIZE;

2583  int result_msg_size;
2584 
2585  if (ut_str_to_oid (oid_str, &oid) < 0)
2586  {
2587  return CCI_ER_OBJECT;
2588  }
2589 
2590  if (col_attr == NULL)
2591  {
2592  col_attr = "";
2593  }

2598

2600  ADD_ARG_OBJECT (&net_buf, &oid);
2601  ADD_ARG_STR (&net_buf, (char *) col_attr, strlen (col_attr) + 1, con_handle->charset);
2602 
2603  if (net_buf.err_code < 0)
2604  {
2605  err_code = net_buf.err_code;
2606  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
2607  return err_code;
2608  }
2609

2611  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
2612  if (err_code < 0)
2613  return err_code;
2614

2616  if (err_code < 0)
2617  return err_code;
2618

2620  {
2621  FREE_MEM (result_msg);
2622  return CCI_ER_COMMUNICATION;
2623  }
2624 
2625  if (set_size)
2626  {
2627  NET_STR_TO_INT (*set_size, result_msg + 4);
2628  }
2629  FREE_MEM (result_msg);
2630 
2631  return 0;
2632 }

2787 int
2788 qe_execute_array (T_REQ_HANDLE * req_handle, T_CON_HANDLE * con_handle, T_CCI_QUERY_RESULT ** qr, T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)
2789 {
2790  T_NET_BUF net_buf;
2791  char func_code = CAS_FC_EXECUTE_ARRAY;
2792  char autocommit_flag;
2793  int err_code = 0;
2794  T_BIND_VALUE cur_cell;
2795  int row, idx;
2796  char *result_msg = NULL;
2797  char *msg;
2798  int result_msg_size;
2799  int remain_size;
2800  int remaining_time = 0;
2801  int shard_id;
2802  T_BROKER_VERSION broker_ver;
2803 
2804  net_buf_init (&net_buf);
2805 
2806  net_buf_cp_str (&net_buf, &func_code, 1);
2807 
2808  ADD_ARG_INT (&net_buf, req_handle->server_handle_id);
2809 
2810  broker_ver = hm_get_broker_version (con_handle);
2811  if (hm_broker_understand_the_protocol (broker_ver, PROTOCOL_V4))
2812  {
2813  if (TIMEOUT_IS_SET (con_handle))
2814  {
2815  remaining_time = con_handle->current_timeout;
2816  remaining_time -= get_elapsed_time (&con_handle->start_time);
2817  if (remaining_time <= 0)
2818  {
2819  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
2820  return CCI_ER_QUERY_TIMEOUT;
2821  }
2822  }
2823  ADD_ARG_INT (&net_buf, remaining_time);
2824  }
2825 
2826  autocommit_flag = (char) con_handle->autocommit_mode;
2827  ADD_ARG_BYTES (&net_buf, &autocommit_flag, 1);
2828 
2829  for (row = 0; row < req_handle->bind_array_size; row++)
2830  {
2831  for (idx = 0; idx < req_handle->num_bind; idx++)
2832  {
2833  cur_cell.flag = BIND_PTR_STATIC;
2834  cur_cell.value = NULL;
2835  cur_cell.size = 0;
2836 
2837  if (req_handle->bind_value[idx].value == NULL)
2838  {
2839  cur_cell.u_type = CCI_U_TYPE_NULL;
2840  }
2841  else if (req_handle->bind_value[idx].null_ind[row])
2842  {
2843  cur_cell.u_type = CCI_U_TYPE_NULL;
2844  }
2845  else
2846  {
2847  char a_type;
2848  T_CCI_U_TYPE u_type;
2849 
2850  a_type = req_handle->bind_value[idx].size;
2851  u_type = req_handle->bind_value[idx].u_type;
2852  err_code = 0;
2853 
2854  switch (a_type)
2855  {
2856  case CCI_A_TYPE_STR:
2857  {
2858  char **value;
2859  value = (char **) req_handle->bind_value[idx].value;
2860  err_code =
2861  bind_value_conversion ((T_CCI_A_TYPE) a_type, u_type, CCI_BIND_PTR, value[row], UNMEASURED_LENGTH,
2862  &cur_cell);
2863  }
2864  break;
2865  case CCI_A_TYPE_BIGINT:
2866  {
2867  INT64 *value;
2868  value = (INT64 *) req_handle->bind_value[idx].value;
2869  err_code =
2870  bind_value_conversion ((T_CCI_A_TYPE) a_type, u_type, CCI_BIND_PTR, &(value[row]),
2871  UNMEASURED_LENGTH, &cur_cell);
2872  }
2873  break;
2874  case CCI_A_TYPE_UBIGINT:
2875  {
2876  UINT64 *value;
2877  value = (UINT64 *) req_handle->bind_value[idx].value;
2878  err_code =
2879  bind_value_conversion ((T_CCI_A_TYPE) a_type, u_type, CCI_BIND_PTR, &(value[row]),
2880  UNMEASURED_LENGTH, &cur_cell);
2881  }
2882  break;
2883  case CCI_A_TYPE_INT:
2884  {
2885  int *value;
2886  value = (int *) req_handle->bind_value[idx].value;
2887  err_code =
2888  bind_value_conversion ((T_CCI_A_TYPE) a_type, u_type, CCI_BIND_PTR, &(value[row]),
2889  UNMEASURED_LENGTH, &cur_cell);
2890  }
2891  break;
2892  case CCI_A_TYPE_UINT:
2893  {
2894  unsigned int *value;
2895  value = (unsigned int *) req_handle->bind_value[idx].value;
2896  err_code =
2897  bind_value_conversion ((T_CCI_A_TYPE) a_type, u_type, CCI_BIND_PTR, &(value[row]),
2898  UNMEASURED_LENGTH, &cur_cell);
2899  }
2900  break;
2901  case CCI_A_TYPE_FLOAT:
2902  {
2903  float *value;
2904  value = (float *) req_handle->bind_value[idx].value;
2905  err_code =
2906  bind_value_conversion ((T_CCI_A_TYPE) a_type, u_type, CCI_BIND_PTR, &(value[row]),
2907  UNMEASURED_LENGTH, &cur_cell);
2908  }
2909  break;
2910  case CCI_A_TYPE_DOUBLE:
2911  {
2912  double *value;
2913  value = (double *) req_handle->bind_value[idx].value;
2914  err_code =
2915  bind_value_conversion ((T_CCI_A_TYPE) a_type, u_type, CCI_BIND_PTR, &(value[row]),
2916  UNMEASURED_LENGTH, &cur_cell);
2917  }
2918  break;
2919  case CCI_A_TYPE_BIT:
2920  {
2921  T_CCI_BIT *value;
2922  value = (T_CCI_BIT *) req_handle->bind_value[idx].value;
2923  err_code =
2924  bind_value_conversion ((T_CCI_A_TYPE) a_type, u_type, CCI_BIND_PTR, &(value[row]),
2925  UNMEASURED_LENGTH, &cur_cell);
2926  }
2927  break;
2928  case CCI_A_TYPE_DATE:
2929  {
2930  T_CCI_DATE *value;
2931  value = (T_CCI_DATE *) req_handle->bind_value[idx].value;
2932  err_code =
2933  bind_value_conversion ((T_CCI_A_TYPE) a_type, u_type, CCI_BIND_PTR, &(value[row]),
2934  UNMEASURED_LENGTH, &cur_cell);
2935  }
2936  break;
2937  case CCI_A_TYPE_DATE_TZ:
2938  {
2939  T_CCI_DATE_TZ *value;
2940  value = (T_CCI_DATE_TZ *) req_handle->bind_value[idx].value;
2941  err_code =
2942  bind_value_conversion ((T_CCI_A_TYPE) a_type, u_type, CCI_BIND_PTR, &(value[row]),
2943  UNMEASURED_LENGTH, &cur_cell);
2944  }
2945  break;
2946  case CCI_A_TYPE_SET:
2947  {
2948  T_SET **value;
2949  value = (T_SET **) req_handle->bind_value[idx].value;
2950  err_code =
2951  bind_value_conversion ((T_CCI_A_TYPE) a_type, u_type, CCI_BIND_PTR, value[row], UNMEASURED_LENGTH,
2952  &cur_cell);
2953  }
2954  break;
2955  case CCI_A_TYPE_BLOB:
2956  case CCI_A_TYPE_CLOB:
2957  {
2958  T_LOB **value;
2959  value = (T_LOB **) req_handle->bind_value[idx].value;
2960  err_code =
2961  bind_value_conversion ((T_CCI_A_TYPE) a_type, u_type, CCI_BIND_PTR, value[row], UNMEASURED_LENGTH,
2962  &cur_cell);
2963  }
2964  break;
2965  default:
2966  err_code = CCI_ER_ATYPE;
2967  } /* end of switch */
2968  if (err_code < 0)
2969  {
2970  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
2971  return err_code;
2972  }
2973  }
2974  bind_value_to_net_buf (&net_buf, cur_cell.u_type, cur_cell.value, cur_cell.size, con_handle->charset, false);
2975  if (cur_cell.flag == BIND_PTR_DYNAMIC)
2976  {
2977  FREE_MEM (cur_cell.value);
2978  }
2979  } /* end of for (idx) */
2980  } /* end of for (row) */
2981 
2982  if (net_buf.err_code < 0)
2983  {
2984  err_code = net_buf.err_code;
2985  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
2986  return err_code;
2987  }
2988 
2989  if (TIMEOUT_IS_SET (con_handle))
2990  {
2991  remaining_time = con_handle->current_timeout;
2992  remaining_time -= get_elapsed_time (&con_handle->start_time);
2993  if (remaining_time <= 0)
2994  {
2995  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
2996  return CCI_ER_QUERY_TIMEOUT;
2997  }
2998  }
2999 
3000  err_code = net_send_msg (con_handle, net_buf.data, net_buf.data_size);
3001  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
3002  if (err_code < 0)
3003  {
3004  return err_code;
3005  }
3006 
3007  err_code = net_recv_msg_timeout (con_handle, &result_msg, &result_msg_size, err_buf, 0);
3008  if (err_code < 0)
3009  {
3010  return err_code;
3011  }
3012 
3013  err_code = execute_array_info_decode (result_msg + 4, result_msg_size - 4, EXECUTE_ARRAY, qr, &remain_size);
3014 
3015  if (err_code >= 0 && hm_broker_understand_the_protocol (broker_ver, PROTOCOL_V5))
3016  {
3017  msg = result_msg + (result_msg_size - remain_size);
3018 
3019  NET_STR_TO_INT (shard_id, msg);
3020  remain_size -= NET_SIZE_INT;
3021  msg += NET_SIZE_INT;
3022 
3023  con_handle->shard_id = shard_id;
3024  req_handle->shard_id = shard_id;
3025  }
3026 
3027  FREE_MEM (result_msg);
3028  return err_code;
3029 }

3155 int
3156 qe_execute_batch (T_CON_HANDLE * con_handle, int num_query, char **sql_stmt, T_CCI_QUERY_RESULT ** qr,
3157  T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)
3158 {
3159  T_NET_BUF net_buf;
3160  char func_code = CAS_FC_EXECUTE_BATCH;
3161  char autocommit_flag;
3162  int err_code;
3163  char *result_msg = NULL;
3164  char *msg;
3165  int result_msg_size;
3166  int sql_len;
3167  int i;
3168  int remain_size;
3169  int remaining_time = 0;
3170  int shard_id;
3171  T_BROKER_VERSION broker_ver;
3172 
3173  net_buf_init (&net_buf);
3174 
3175  net_buf_cp_str (&net_buf, &func_code, 1);
3176 
3177  /* set AutoCommitMode is FALSE */
3178  autocommit_flag = (char) con_handle->autocommit_mode;
3179  ADD_ARG_BYTES (&net_buf, &autocommit_flag, 1);
3180 
3181  broker_ver = hm_get_broker_version (con_handle);
3182  if (hm_broker_understand_the_protocol (broker_ver, PROTOCOL_V4))
3183  {
3184  if (TIMEOUT_IS_SET (con_handle))
3185  {
3186  remaining_time = con_handle->current_timeout;
3187  remaining_time -= get_elapsed_time (&con_handle->start_time);
3188  if (remaining_time <= 0)
3189  {
3190  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
3191  return CCI_ER_QUERY_TIMEOUT;
3192  }
3193  }
3194  ADD_ARG_INT (&net_buf, remaining_time);
3195  }
3196 
3197  for (i = 0; i < num_query; i++)
3198  {
3199  sql_len = strlen (sql_stmt[i]) + 1;
3200  ADD_ARG_STR (&net_buf, sql_stmt[i], sql_len, con_handle->charset);
3201  }
3202 
3203  if (net_buf.err_code < 0)
3204  {
3205  err_code = net_buf.err_code;
3206  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
3207  return err_code;
3208  }
3209 
3210  if (TIMEOUT_IS_SET (con_handle))
3211  {
3212  remaining_time = con_handle->current_timeout;
3213  remaining_time -= get_elapsed_time (&con_handle->start_time);
3214  if (remaining_time <= 0)
3215  {
3216  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
3217  return CCI_ER_QUERY_TIMEOUT;
3218  }
3219  }
3220 
3221  err_code = net_send_msg (con_handle, net_buf.data, net_buf.data_size);
3222  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
3223  if (err_code < 0)
3224  {
3225  return err_code;
3226  }
3227 
3228  err_code = net_recv_msg_timeout (con_handle, &result_msg, &result_msg_size, err_buf, 0);
3229  if (err_code < 0)
3230  {
3231  return err_code;
3232  }
3233 
3234  err_code = execute_array_info_decode (result_msg + 4, result_msg_size - 4, EXECUTE_BATCH, qr, &remain_size);
3235 
3236  if (err_code >= 0 && hm_broker_understand_the_protocol (broker_ver, PROTOCOL_V5))
3237  {
3238  msg = result_msg + (result_msg_size - remain_size);
3239 
3240  NET_STR_TO_INT (shard_id, msg);
3241  remain_size -= NET_SIZE_INT;
3242  msg += NET_SIZE_INT;
3243 
3244  con_handle->shard_id = shard_id;
3245  }
3246 
3247  FREE_MEM (result_msg);
3248 
3249  return err_code;
3250 }

3252 int
3253 qe_get_data_str (T_VALUE_BUF * conv_val_buf, T_CCI_U_TYPE u_type, char *col_value_p, int col_val_size, void *value,
3254  int *indicator)
3255 {
3256  assert (u_type >= CCI_U_TYPE_FIRST && u_type <= CCI_U_TYPE_LAST);
3257 
3258  switch (u_type)
3259  {
3260  case CCI_U_TYPE_CHAR:
3261  case CCI_U_TYPE_STRING:
3262  case CCI_U_TYPE_NCHAR:
3263  case CCI_U_TYPE_VARNCHAR:
3264  case CCI_U_TYPE_NUMERIC:
3265  case CCI_U_TYPE_ENUM:
3266  {
3267  *((char **) value) = col_value_p;
3268  *indicator = col_val_size - 1;
3269  }
3270  return 0;
3271  case CCI_U_TYPE_BIT:
3272  case CCI_U_TYPE_VARBIT:
3273  {
3274  if (hm_conv_value_buf_alloc (conv_val_buf, col_val_size * 2 + 2) < 0)
3275  {
3276  return CCI_ER_NO_MORE_MEMORY;
3277  }
3278  ut_bit_to_str (col_value_p, col_val_size, (char *) conv_val_buf->data, col_val_size * 2 + 2);
3279  }
3280  break;
3281  case CCI_U_TYPE_BIGINT:
3282  {
3283  INT64 data;
3284 
3285  qe_get_data_bigint (u_type, col_value_p, &data);
3286 
3287  if (hm_conv_value_buf_alloc (conv_val_buf, 128) < 0)
3288  {
3289  return CCI_ER_NO_MORE_MEMORY;
3290  }
3291  ut_int_to_str (data, (char *) conv_val_buf->data, 128);
3292  }
3293  break;
3294  case CCI_U_TYPE_UBIGINT:
3295  {
3296  UINT64 data;
3297 
3298  qe_get_data_ubigint (u_type, col_value_p, &data);
3299 
3300  if (hm_conv_value_buf_alloc (conv_val_buf, 128) < 0)
3301  {
3302  return CCI_ER_NO_MORE_MEMORY;
3303  }
3304  ut_uint_to_str (data, (char *) conv_val_buf->data, 128);
3305  }
3306  break;
3307  case CCI_U_TYPE_INT:
3308  case CCI_U_TYPE_SHORT:
3309  {
3310  int data;
3311 
3312  qe_get_data_int (u_type, col_value_p, &data);
3313 
3314  if (hm_conv_value_buf_alloc (conv_val_buf, 128) < 0)
3315  {
3316  return CCI_ER_NO_MORE_MEMORY;
3317  }
3318  ut_int_to_str (data, (char *) conv_val_buf->data, 128);
3319  }
3320  break;
3321  case CCI_U_TYPE_UINT:
3322  case CCI_U_TYPE_USHORT:
3323  {
3324  unsigned int data;
3325 
3326  qe_get_data_uint (u_type, col_value_p, &data);
3327 
3328  if (hm_conv_value_buf_alloc (conv_val_buf, 128) < 0)
3329  {
3330  return CCI_ER_NO_MORE_MEMORY;
3331  }
3332  ut_uint_to_str (data, (char *) conv_val_buf->data, 128);
3333  }
3334  break;
3335  case CCI_U_TYPE_MONETARY:

3362  case CCI_U_TYPE_DATE:

3365  case CCI_U_TYPE_DATETIME:

3367  T_CCI_DATE data;
3368

3373  return CCI_ER_NO_MORE_MEMORY;
3374  }
3375  ut_date_to_str (&data, u_type, (char *) conv_val_buf->data, 128);
3376  }
3377  break;
3378  case CCI_U_TYPE_TIMESTAMPTZ:
3379  case CCI_U_TYPE_TIMESTAMPLTZ:
3380  case CCI_U_TYPE_DATETIMETZ:
3381  case CCI_U_TYPE_DATETIMELTZ:
3382  {
3383  T_CCI_DATE_TZ data_tz;
3384 
3385  qe_get_data_date_tz (u_type, col_value_p, &data_tz, col_val_size);
3386

3388  {
3389  return CCI_ER_NO_MORE_MEMORY;
3390  }
3391  ut_date_tz_to_str (&data_tz, u_type, (char *) conv_val_buf->data, 128);
3392  }
3393  break;
3394  case CCI_U_TYPE_SET:
3395  case CCI_U_TYPE_MULTISET:
3396  case CCI_U_TYPE_SEQUENCE:
3397  {
3398  int err_code;
3399  T_SET *set;
3400 
3401  err_code = get_data_set (u_type, col_value_p, &set, col_val_size);
3402  if (err_code < 0)
3403  {
3404  return err_code;
3405  }
3406 
3407  err_code = t_set_to_str (set, conv_val_buf);
3408  t_set_free (set);
3409  if (err_code < 0)
3410  {
3411  return err_code;
3412  }
3413  }
3414  break;
3415  case CCI_U_TYPE_OBJECT:
3416  {
3417  T_OBJECT data;
3418  if (hm_conv_value_buf_alloc (conv_val_buf, 128) < 0)
3419  {
3420  return CCI_ER_NO_MORE_MEMORY;
3421  }
3422  NET_STR_TO_OBJECT (data, col_value_p);
3423  ut_oid_to_str (&data, (char *) conv_val_buf->data);
3424  }
3425  break;
3426  case CCI_U_TYPE_BLOB:
3427  case CCI_U_TYPE_CLOB:
3428  {
3429  int err_code;
3430  T_LOB *lob = NULL;
3431 
3432  err_code = qe_get_data_lob (u_type, col_value_p, col_val_size, (void *) &lob);
3433  if (err_code < 0)
3434  {
3435  return err_code;
3436  }
3437  if (hm_conv_value_buf_alloc (conv_val_buf, col_val_size) < 0)
3438  {
3439  FREE_MEM (lob);
3440  return CCI_ER_NO_MORE_MEMORY;
3441  }
3442  ut_lob_to_str (lob, (char *) conv_val_buf->data, col_val_size);
3443  FREE_MEM (lob);
3444  }
3445  break;
3446  default:
3447  return CCI_ER_TYPE_CONVERSION;
3448  }
3449 
3450  *((char **) value) = (char *) conv_val_buf->data;
3451  *indicator = strlen ((char *) conv_val_buf->data);
3452 
3453  return 0;
3454 }

3793  case CCI_U_TYPE_UINT:
3794  {
3795  unsigned int ui_val;
3796  NET_STR_TO_UINT (ui_val, col_value_p);
3797  data = (float) ui_val;
3798  }
3799 
3800  break;
3801  case CCI_U_TYPE_SHORT:
3802  {
3803  short s_val;
3804  NET_STR_TO_SHORT (s_val, col_value_p);
3805  data = (float) s_val;
3806  }
3807  break;
3808  case CCI_U_TYPE_USHORT:
3809  {
3810  unsigned short us_val;
3811  NET_STR_TO_USHORT (us_val, col_value_p);
3812  data = (float) us_val;
3813  }
3814  break;
3815  case CCI_U_TYPE_MONETARY:
3816  case CCI_U_TYPE_DOUBLE:
3817  {
3818  double d_val;
3819  NET_STR_TO_DOUBLE (d_val, col_value_p);
3820  data = (float) d_val;
3821  }
3822  break;
3823  case CCI_U_TYPE_FLOAT:
3824  {
3825  NET_STR_TO_FLOAT (data, col_value_p);
3826  }
3827  break;
3828  default:
3829  return CCI_ER_TYPE_CONVERSION;
3830  }
3831 
3832  *((float *) value) = data;
3833  return 0;
3834 }

3872  data = (double) i_val;
3873  }
3874  break;

3880  }
3881  break;

3886  data = (double) s_val;
3887  }
3888  break;

4007 int
4008 qe_get_data_req_handle (T_CON_HANDLE * con_handle, T_REQ_HANDLE * req_handle, char *col_value_p, void *value)
4009 {
4010  T_REQ_HANDLE *out_req_handle = NULL;
4011  T_NET_BUF net_buf;
4012  char func_code = CAS_FC_MAKE_OUT_RS;
4013  int error = CCI_ER_NO_ERROR;
4014  int statement_id = -1;
4015  int srv_handle = 0;
4016  char *result_msg = NULL;
4017  int result_msg_size;
4018 
4019  if (req_handle == NULL)
4020  {
4021  return CCI_ER_REQ_HANDLE;
4022  }
4023 
4024  if (req_handle->stmt_type != CUBRID_STMT_CALL_SP)
4025  {
4026  return CCI_ER_TYPE_CONVERSION;
4027  }
4028 
4029  statement_id = hm_req_handle_alloc (con_handle, &out_req_handle);
4030  if (statement_id < 0)
4031  {
4032  error = statement_id;
4033  goto get_data_error;
4034  }
4035 
4036  NET_STR_TO_INT (srv_handle, col_value_p);
4037 
4038  net_buf_init (&net_buf);
4039  net_buf_cp_str (&net_buf, &func_code, 1);
4040  ADD_ARG_INT (&net_buf, srv_handle);
4041 
4042  error = net_send_msg (con_handle, net_buf.data, net_buf.data_size);
4043  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
4044  if (error < 0)
4045  {
4046  error = CCI_ER_COMMUNICATION;
4047  goto get_data_error;
4048  }
4049 
4050  error = net_recv_msg_timeout (con_handle, &result_msg, &result_msg_size, NULL, 0);
4051  if (error < 0)
4052  {
4053  goto get_data_error;
4054  }
4055 
4056  result_msg_size -= 4;
4057  error = out_rs_info_decode (result_msg + 4, &result_msg_size, out_req_handle);
4058  if (error < 0)
4059  {
4060  goto get_data_error;
4061  }
4062 
4063  if (result_msg != NULL)
4064  {
4065  FREE_MEM (result_msg);
4066  }
4067 
4068  map_open_ots (statement_id, &out_req_handle->mapped_stmt_id);
4069  *((int *) value) = out_req_handle->mapped_stmt_id;
4070 
4071  return 0;
4072 
4073 get_data_error:
4074  if (result_msg != NULL)
4075  {
4076  FREE_MEM (result_msg);
4077  }
4078 
4079  if (out_req_handle != NULL)
4080  {
4081  hm_req_handle_free (con_handle, out_req_handle);
4082  out_req_handle = NULL;
4083  }
4084 
4085  return error;
4086 }

4445  {
4446  return err_code;
4447  }
4448 
4449  handle_size = net_recv_msg (con_handle, &result_msg, &result_msg_size, err_buf);
4450  if (handle_size < 0)
4451  {
4452  return handle_size;
4453  }
4454  else if (handle_size == 0)
4455  {
4456  return CCI_ER_COMMUNICATION;
4457  }
4458 
4459  cur_p = result_msg;
4460  cur_p += 4;
4461 
4462  new_lob = (T_LOB *) MALLOC (sizeof (T_LOB));
4463  if (new_lob == NULL)
4464  {
4465  FREE_MEM (result_msg);
4466  return CCI_ER_NO_MORE_MEMORY;
4467  }
4468 
4469  new_lob->type = type;
4470  new_lob->handle_size = handle_size;
4471  new_lob->handle = (char *) MALLOC (new_lob->handle_size);
4472  if (new_lob->handle == NULL)
4473  {
4474  FREE_MEM (result_msg);
4475  FREE_MEM (new_lob);
4476  return CCI_ER_NO_MORE_MEMORY;
4477  }
4478 
4479  memcpy (new_lob->handle, cur_p, new_lob->handle_size);
4480 
4481  if (result_msg_size < NET_SIZE_INT + new_lob->handle_size)
4482  {
4483  FREE_MEM (result_msg);
4484  FREE_MEM (new_lob->handle);
4485  FREE_MEM (new_lob);
4486  return CCI_ER_COMMUNICATION;
4487  }
4488 
4489  *lob = new_lob;
4490 
4491  FREE_MEM (result_msg);
4492  return CCI_ER_NO_ERROR;
4493 }

4495 int
4496 qe_lob_write (T_CON_HANDLE * con_handle, T_LOB * lob, INT64 start_pos, int length, const char *buf,
4497  T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)
4498 {
4499  T_NET_BUF net_buf;
4500  char func_code = CAS_FC_LOB_WRITE;
4501  int err_code = 0;
4502  char *result_msg = NULL;
4503  int result_msg_size;
4504  INT64 lob_size;
4505  int bytes_written;
4506 
4507  net_buf_init (&net_buf);
4508  net_buf_cp_str (&net_buf, &func_code, 1);
4509 
4510  ADD_ARG_BYTES (&net_buf, lob->handle, lob->handle_size);
4511  ADD_ARG_INT64 (&net_buf, start_pos);
4512  ADD_ARG_BYTES (&net_buf, buf, length);
4513  if (net_buf.err_code < 0)
4514  {
4515  err_code = net_buf.err_code;
4516  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
4517  return err_code;
4518  }
4519 
4520  err_code = net_send_msg (con_handle, net_buf.data, net_buf.data_size);
4521  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
4522  if (err_code < 0)
4523  {
4524  return err_code;
4525  }
4526 
4527  bytes_written = net_recv_msg (con_handle, &result_msg, &result_msg_size, err_buf);
4528  if (bytes_written < 0)
4529  {
4530  return bytes_written;
4531  }
4532 
4533  if (result_msg_size < NET_SIZE_INT || bytes_written > length)
4534  {
4535  FREE_MEM (result_msg);
4536  return CCI_ER_COMMUNICATION;
4537  }
4538 
4539  lob_size = t_lob_get_size (lob->handle);
4540  if (start_pos + bytes_written > lob_size)
4541  {
4542  t_lob_set_size (lob, start_pos + bytes_written);
4543  }
4544 
4545  FREE_MEM (result_msg);
4546  return bytes_written;
4547 }

4564  ADD_ARG_INT (&net_buf, length);

4603 {

4606  char *result_msg = NULL;
4607  int result_msg_size;
4608  int err_code;
4609  int num_shard;
4610 
4611  if (shard_info)
4612  {
4613  *shard_info = NULL;
4614  }
4615 
4616  net_buf_init (&net_buf);
4617  net_buf_cp_str (&net_buf, &func_code, 1);
4618  if (net_buf.err_code < 0)
4619  {
4620  err_code = net_buf.err_code;
4621  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
4622  return err_code;
4623  }
4624 
4625  err_code = net_send_msg (con_handle, net_buf.data, net_buf.data_size);
4626  net_buf_clear (&net_buf);
4627  if (err_code < 0)

4629  return err_code;

4640  if (num_shard)
4641  {

4643  if (err_code < 0)
4644  {
4645  num_shard = err_code;
4646  }
4647  }
4648 
4649  FREE_MEM (result_msg);
4650 
4651  return num_shard;
4652 }

4654 int
4655 qe_shard_info_free (T_CCI_SHARD_INFO * shard_info)
4656 {
4657  T_CCI_SHARD_INFO *cur_shard_info;
4658  int prev_shard_id = SHARD_ID_INVALID;
4659 
4660  for (cur_shard_info = shard_info; cur_shard_info->shard_id != SHARD_ID_INVALID; cur_shard_info++)
4661  {
4662  if (cur_shard_info->shard_id <= prev_shard_id)
4663  {
4664  assert (cur_shard_info->shard_id == SHARD_ID_INVALID); /* fence */
4665  break;
4666  }
4667 
4668  FREE_MEM (cur_shard_info->db_name);
4669  FREE_MEM (cur_shard_info->db_server);
4670 
4671  if (cur_shard_info != shard_info)
4672  {
4673  prev_shard_id = cur_shard_info->shard_id;
4674  }
4675  }
4676 
4677  FREE_MEM (shard_info);
4678  return CCI_ER_NO_ERROR;
4679 }

4701 #if defined(WINDOWS)

4703 encode_string (const char *str, int size, char **target, char *charset)
4704 {

4706  char *tmp_string;
4707  BSTR bstrCode;
4708  int wincode;

4713  {
4714  return 0;
4715  }

4720  {
4721  return CCI_ER_NO_MORE_MEMORY;
4722  }

4724

4726  tmp_string = (char *) MALLOC (sizeof (char) * (nLength + 1));
4727  if (tmp_string == NULL)
4728  {
4729  return CCI_ER_NO_MORE_MEMORY;

4731

4733  if (target)
4734  {
4735  *target = tmp_string;
4736  }
4737 
4738  SysFreeString (bstrCode);

4755  {
4756  return 0;

4805 static int
4806 prepare_info_decode (char *buf, int *size, T_REQ_HANDLE * req_handle)
4807 {
4808  int num_bind_info;
4809  int num_col_info;
4810  int remain_size = *size;
4811  char stmt_type;
4812  char updatable_flag = 0;
4813  char *cur_p = buf;
4814  T_CCI_COL_INFO *col_info = NULL;
4815  int result_cache_lifetime;
4816 
4817  if (remain_size < NET_SIZE_INT)
4818  {
4819  return CCI_ER_COMMUNICATION;
4820  }
4821 
4822  NET_STR_TO_INT (result_cache_lifetime, cur_p);
4823  remain_size -= NET_SIZE_INT;
4824  cur_p += NET_SIZE_INT;
4825 
4826  if (remain_size < NET_SIZE_BYTE)
4827  {
4828  return CCI_ER_COMMUNICATION;
4829  }
4830 
4831  NET_STR_TO_BYTE (stmt_type, cur_p);
4832  remain_size -= NET_SIZE_BYTE;
4833  cur_p += NET_SIZE_BYTE;
4834 
4835  if (remain_size < NET_SIZE_INT)
4836  {
4837  return CCI_ER_COMMUNICATION;
4838  }
4839 
4840  NET_STR_TO_INT (num_bind_info, cur_p);
4841  remain_size -= NET_SIZE_INT;
4842  cur_p += NET_SIZE_INT;
4843 
4844  if (remain_size < NET_SIZE_BYTE)
4845  {
4846  return CCI_ER_COMMUNICATION;
4847  }
4848 
4849  NET_STR_TO_BYTE (updatable_flag, cur_p);
4850  remain_size -= NET_SIZE_BYTE;
4851  cur_p += NET_SIZE_BYTE;
4852 
4853  num_col_info = get_column_info (cur_p, &remain_size, &col_info, NULL, true);
4854  if (num_col_info < 0)
4855  {
4856  assert (col_info == NULL);
4857  return num_col_info;
4858  }
4859 
4860  req_handle_col_info_free (req_handle);
4861 
4862  req_handle->num_bind = num_bind_info;
4863  req_handle->num_col_info = num_col_info;
4864  req_handle->col_info = col_info;
4865  req_handle->stmt_type = (T_CCI_CUBRID_STMT) stmt_type;
4866  req_handle->first_stmt_type = req_handle->stmt_type;
4867  req_handle->updatable_flag = updatable_flag;
4868 
4869  *size = remain_size;
4870  return 0;
4871 }
